title: lasagna(homemade sauce)
directions: Add oil, onion, celery stalks to hamburger and cook until brown, then add tomato juice, tomato soup, sugar, salt, pepper, mushrooms, Italian seasoning and oregano.
Simmer for 3/4 hour. Cook lasagna, then drain.

title: sopaipilla mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir with wire whisk until blended. Use pastry blender and cut shortening into flour mixture.
Makes 8 cups.
Store in airtight container.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Brown cubed beef in electric skillet or pan. Add the brown gravy mix and 1 cup water. Stir until bubbly and all mixture is dissolved. Add 1 can brown gravy to mixture and turn to simmer. Cook for a few hours or until beef is very tender.
Prepare rice according to directions. Add the butter or margarine to the rice. When beef is done or tender, serve over the rice.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box, then fold in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers, pudding and graham crackers.
Frost top layer of graham crackers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray large casserole dish with Pam or grease well.
Layer bottom of dish with shredded cabbage.
Brown ground beef and onion together.
Pour in rice and mix.
Spread beef mixture over cabbage.
Mix one can of soup and one can of water.
Pour over beef mixture.
Cover dish with aluminum foil. Bake for 1 hour.
Very low in calories!

title: mild chow chow
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Mix with 3/4 cup salt.
Let stand overnight; drain the mixed spices in bag.
Add sugar, vinegar, spices, mustard seed and water.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, then simmer until just done.
Remove spice bag.
Add enough water to cornstarch so it is completely dissolved.
Add to chow chow and stir well.
Cut off heat and pack into boiled jars and seal at once.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put 1/2 nuts in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into ball and roll in the other half of nuts.
Chill.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Add egg yolks.
Cook until thick; add vanilla.
Pour in cooked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue, using 3 egg whites.
Bake in 325° oven until meringue is slightly browned.

title: holiday brunch casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan put 2 layers of buttered bread.
Mix together and pour over the bread bacon, Cheddar cheese, eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup milk and the bananas; mix until flour is dampened or 2 minutes.
Add eggs, nuts and remaining milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes or until done.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, molasses and water thoroughly. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until almost no imprint remains when touched with finger.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine
sour
cream,
lemon
juice,
sugar,
salt
and drained, crushed pineapple,
banana pieces and enough red food color to give a pink tint.
Lightly fold in nuts and cherries. Spoon into fluted paper
muffin
cups
(large size) which have been placed in 3-inch
muffin
cup
pans.
Freeze.
Cover with plastic wrap and store
in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving to loosen paper cups from pan.
Peel off paper cup and
place
salad
on
lettuce leaves.
Fills 12 large paper muffin cups.

title: sherry'd rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add the bouillon, rice and sherry.
Mix well.
Pour contents into a casserole. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Very easy, but elegant and gourmet.

title: oatmeal pie #1
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, then add rest of ingredients. Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake 10 minutes in hot oven at 425°, then turn down to low (325°).
Bake 30 minutes longer until done. Cool on rack.

title: peanut butter and jelly party pie
directions: In large bowl, combine peanut butter and corn syrup; blend well.
Stir in cereal; press mixture evenly and firmly around sides and bottom of 9-inch pie pan with lightly buttered spatula. Chill 10 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onions; add green chilies and garlic.
Stir in flour and chicken broth.
Add salt and cumin. Simmer 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°; grease cake pan.
Fry tortillas slightly in hot oil.
Dip into sauce.
Roll chicken and cheese in each tortilla.
Pour remaining sauce and cream over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes. Garnish with lettuce, green onions and tomatoes.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Spray 8x12 pan with Pam.
Pour in cheese and smooth out.
Place peppers evenly all over.
Beat eggs till frothy.
Pour over cheese. Cook at 350 til lightly browned.
Cool and cut into small squares. Makes 2 doz.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Unroll crescent rolls. Place chicken strip and cheese strip in each crescent roll. Roll up and place in 9 x 13 pan.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Stir in other ingredients.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat
oven

and	salt;

In	large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar	and

Stir in morsels and nuts.
Spread dough into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375°	for
20 to 25 minutes.	Cool completely.
Cut into 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda into medium bowl.
Beat 2 eggs in large bowl until foamy.
Add sugar slowly and beat until thick and light.
Melt shortening in boiling water. Mix in orange juice.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture alternately with orange juice mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: tallerina
directions: Cook noodles in water and drain.
Saute onions, garlic and green pepper.
Add meat and saute crumbled.
Mix noodles and meat/vegetable mixture together.
Add corn, olives, tomatoes, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, olive juice, salt and pepper. Mix 1/2 of the cheese into this mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over all.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Excellent with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: country corn casserole
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring vegetables and water to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes or until tender; drain.
In a saucepan over medium heat, saute the onion in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Add soup and milk; stir until smooth.
Add cracker crumbs and cooked vegetables; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: eggplant and zucchini casserole(colorful, delicious dish)
directions: Place eggplant, zucchini, tomato, onion into a large skillet. Season with thyme, salt, and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 2 quart casserole dish.
Layer vegetables, cheese, and dry stuffing mix in the dish until all ingredients have been used ending with cheese.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes.

title: hot spiced instant tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in a covered glass jar. Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Delicious on a cold winter's day.
A great gift idea.
Yields 3 to 4 cups instant tea mix.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oleo and oats; cover and set aside. Add white and brown sugar to eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add eggs mixture and dry ingredients to oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.

title: cherry cola dessert
directions: *Choose your favorites: blueberries, strawberries and raspberries are a good combo, but I have used cantaloupe, peaches, nectarines and blackberries. Choose 3 that will provide different colors in your trifle.

title: grouper in white wine
directions: Marinate grouper in wine for one hour.
Drain and dredge in flour.
Dip into mixture of eggs and Parmesan.
Melt butter in skillet; add garlic.
Saute fillets until done.
Remove fish from skillet and pour wine into skillet.
Heat until wine is warm and mixes well with butter in pan.
Pour over fish and serve.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 5 minutes. Slice tomatoes in bottom of pie shell. Add onions on top of this.
Add bacon on top of the onions. Mix mayonnaise and cheese together.
Add this for pie topping. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, mangos and onions.
Cover with ice and the salt.
Let stand 3 hours and drain well.
Add to vinegar mixture, heat and can.

title: ritz torte
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; gradually add sugar.
Mix other ingredients together and add to egg whites.
Fold all ingredients. Grease 9-inch pan and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add Cool Whip to top it as serving.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter in milk, pour over bread crumbs.
Mix well and add to squash, season with salt and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs and pour into greased baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: tunnel o'fudge cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, 2 at a time. Fold in by hand the flour, frosting and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake adele
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs and beat.
Add all dry ingredients, raisins and pumpkin; beat for 10 minutes.
Flour greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: marinating sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate meat for 12 hours.

title: vegie wedgies
directions: Cover the bottom of jelly roll pan with crescent rolls, spreading over entire bottom.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dry dressing together; spread over rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables over top.
Press down. Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top before cutting into squares.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Blend first four ingredients in a large bowl.
Add beans.
Add onion,
pimento and celery.
Store in a tight-sealing bowl in refrigerator.
Flavor improves with age.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; add milk gradually.
Then, add beaten egg yolks and butter.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into a baked pastry shell.
Cool. Refrigerate.

title: dressing for poultry
directions: Dice bread or break apart and dry in a very low (200°) oven. Cool.
Meanwhile, melt 1 or 1 1/2 sticks margarine and saute cut-up liver and heart.
Add chopped celery and onion.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cool.
When both cool, mix thoroughly together. Add beaten eggs, to which you have
added a little milk, sage, salt and pepper.
Mix; add a little more milk.
Let stand 1 hour or overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
If it looks dry, add a little more milk before stuffing bird.
Must be wet but not soggy.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows; simmer until dissolved and add mayonnaise, evaporated milk, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in a shallow pan and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs
and oil well.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Then stir in vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: beaten biscuits(alabama tech extension service)
directions: Mix and sift flour and salt.
Work in fat with pastry blender. Moisten to a stiff dough.
Grind in a kneader 15 minutes or beat with a rolling pin until smooth and well blistered, continuing folding over the dough to incorporate air.
Roll about 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with a small biscuit cutter and prick with a fork. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brownie fruit pizza
directions: Prepare brownies as box says. Put on a greased pizza pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool. Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Spread on brownie pizza. Drain pineapple (save juice to dip banana in to keep from turning brown). Place all fruit sliced on top of pizza. Melt chocolate and butter and drizzle over top of fruit.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Drop rounded tablespoon of mixture into shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Add sugar to cream cheese slowly.
Add other ingredients and just enough milk to blend into a very heavy paste, about 1 or 2 tablespoons.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Roll into small balls and then roll into cinnamon.

title: congealed salad(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Put pineapple in boiler. Heat very hot, but do not let it boil. Take off the stove and put in jello. Stir until well dissolved. Add buttermilk and stir good. Pour this into dish; fold in carton of Cool Whip. Put in refrigerator and let congeal.

title: oriental yule mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large roasting pan, combine almonds, chow mein noodles and rice crackers.
Beat together oil, soy sauce, lemon juice and ginger.
Pour over almond mixture and toss to coat.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.

title: black bean rice
directions: In large skillet spray nonfat cooking spray, then add black beans, crushed tomatoes, mushrooms and onions.
Bring to boil. Let boil for 10 minutes, then add cup of uncooked rice and seasoning.
Let simmer for another 5 to 10 minutes until rice is tender.
May add Polish sausage or hamburger, if desired.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix Coke and ketchup.
Place pork chops in baking dish.
Cover with Coke mixture.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: In a large bowl put the warm water and yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and mix flour.
Knead 8 minutes.
Put in a bowl and let it rise until it looks double in its size. Grease cookie sheet, shape them and paint them with egg yolk and sprinkle with salt.
Bake on 475° for 10 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Prepare crepes or bring to room temperature if refrigerated or frozen.
Melt butter in a wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add peaches, lemon peel, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Cook, gently turning occasionally with a wide spatula, until peaches begin to soften and look translucent (about 7 minutes).
Gradually sprinkle in sugar and cook, stirring gently, for 2 more minutes.
Sprinkle brandy over peaches; continue cooking until liquid is thickened. Remove from heat and let cool slightly.

title: mrs. wilkes' boarding house trifle
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Let stand while breaking cake into bite-sized pieces.
Add sherry to pudding and pour over cake. Stir whipped cream through mixture.
Put mixture in a trifle bowl or clear glass bowl and garnish with cut up cherries.
Serves 8.

title: red punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Add juices and mix well. Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in a large saucepan.
Add chopped onions, salad mix and tomatoes.
Simmer until liquid is evaporated. Mix into tomato mixture, tomato paste, water, sugar, 1/4 cup parsley, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, fennel seed, basil and 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Mix hamburg and bread crumbs in large bowl.
Add 1/4 cup milk, eggs, 1/4 cup parsley, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix with hands until well moistened.
Brown in 2 tablespoons margarine. Drain and add to tomato mixture.

title: cajun pie
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour in an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: herbed fish and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees or grill to medium-high.
Spray foil with nonstick cooking spray.
Center one fish fillet on each sheet of foil.
Top with green onions; place frozen vegetables around fish.
Sprinkle fish with thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper. Top with margarine.
Bring up foil sides.
Double fold top and ends to seal packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside. Repeat to make two jackets. Bake 18-20 minutes on a cookie sheet in oven or grill 10-12 minutes in covered grill.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Heat olive oil in large soup pan over moderate heat. Add leeks and cook just until tender. Add flour and stir to blend with the oil.
Add potatoes and water to cover. Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add seasoning to taste. Serve hot, preferably with a warm bread.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind the 5 vegetables in food chopper.
Let set 1/2 hour. Drain.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Jar and seal.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix ingredients together and in thick saucepan, cook until peanuts pop and turn a golden brown.
Remove from heat and add soda and stir real good.
Pour in a well buttered pan.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: quick grilled scallops
directions: Heat butter in large frying pan.
Add scallops and season with pepper.
Cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes over medium-high heat, turning once.
Add mushrooms and shallot to pan; continue cooking covered for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve immediately.

title: elegant onion rings
directions: In a small bowl blend oil and flour with fork.
Add egg then milk, a little at a time.
Stir in garlic salt, beat until smooth. Batter will be thin.
Peel onions, cut into slices.
Separate into rings.
Put several rings at a time into paper sack with 1 cup of flour.
Shake gently to coat.
Put rings into batter. Remove one at a time with a fork and drop into hot oil (375°). Turn once; take up when golden brown on both sides.
Salt to taste.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Prepare lemon cake mix according to directions. Bake.
Cool about 30 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with a fork.
Prepare jello. Pour mixture into holes in cake.
Cool completely.

title: caramel cheesecake
directions: Butter 9-inch round cake pan.
Pur topping into pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese smooth.
Add in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition. Carefully pour cheese mixture over caramel topping.
Set pan into a larger pan.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 inch boiling water to large pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Then separate from pan with a knife onto serving plate.
Cover and chill.

title: salt free seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in capped shaker or jar. Store in dry place.
Adjust amount to taste.
Multiply recipe for desired amounts.
Makes 1 tablespoon.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes. Start counting when mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Blend well and drop by spoonful onto greased waxed paper.

title: tex mex tofu lasagna
directions: Saute tofu, garlic and onion in oil.
Stir in Mexican seasoning packets.
When onions begin to soften, add tomato puree and frozen vegetables.
Mix well.
Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Line the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish with 2 of the 6 tortillas.
Layer 1/2 of the tomato tofu mixture.
Top with 1/2 of all cheeses, follow with cilantro, then jalapeno peppers.
Repeat once with remaining ingredients, ending with the last 2 tortillas and salsa.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheeses melt, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale in a gallon plastic container and freeze.
When ready to use, let thaw enough to get a spoon down into the middle.
Put in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: coney sauce
directions: Fry onions in Crisco; add hamburger and stir until done.
To keep it fine (very fine), add spices and tomato juice.
Add water to thin.
If want hotter sauce, add more chili powder.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients except strawberries until soft dough forms.
Spread in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.
Split each piece horizontally.
Fil and top each serving with strawberries.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup soup.
Mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire sauce and pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring often.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Place marshmallows in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased. Pour cake batter over marshmallows.
Mix together rhubarb, sugar and water and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello. Pour over cake and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cobb salad
directions: Chop all greens; dice tomatoes, also finely dice chicken, avocado and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and toss with the dressing.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, sunflower seeds, raisins, and bacon. In separate bowl, mix sugar, vinegar, and mayonnaise. Pour dressing over salad and toss lightly.

title: auntie's apple crisp
directions: Slice apples or pears. Pour water over and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Mix flour, sugar and egg. Sprinkle over apples.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.

title: david's five star chili
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, salsa, milk, tortillas and half the cheese.
Spoon into 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serves 4. Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
30 minutes.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add milk, salt, Tabasco sauce together.
Pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter and cover tightly with foil.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 400°.
Remove foil. Add cheese and green chillies.
Bake until cheese is melted, then serve.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Add 1/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons water to melted chocolate. Cream the butter well.
Add remaining 2 cups sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla, then egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add chocolate mixture; blend thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Fold in egg whites, beaten until stiff but not dry.
Pour into 3 greased round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until done.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then turn out on racks to cool.
Put layers together with filling; spread the top and sides of cake with a chocolate cream cheese frosting.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Blend together salt, soups, milk, celery and pimentos.
Pour mixture over rice. Season chicken to taste and put on top of rice.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours. Remove foil to brown.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet; fry chicken until browned.
Drain; place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender; stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°
about 1 hour or until chicken is done, basting occasionally.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican meatloaf
directions: In skillet, brown onion, peppers, garlic and seasoning packet in oil.
Combine these ingredients with remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Shape mixture in a loaf and bake until browned, 45 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: aunt betty's ivory fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream.
Beat until the mixture loses glossy look. Pour into buttered dish. When cool, cut into pieces.

title: mom's pepper relish
directions: Remove	stems and seeds from bell peppers.
Peel onions and quarter.
Grind peppers and onions, saving juice.
Combine with remaining
ingredients
and
boil 30 minutes.
Stir frequently. Pack in jars and seal.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Crumble brownies.
Prepare mousse mix according to package directions, but do not chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet on medium-high heat. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to boil; reduce to lowest heat and simmer covered for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: chick-n-broccoli pot pies
directions: Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Place each one in ungreased muffin cup; press dough to cover bottom and sides, forming 1/4-inch rim.
Spoon about a tablespoon cheese, then cereal into each cup.
Dot each with margarine.
Combine chicken, soup and broccoli; spoon about 1/3 cup over cereal.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuit cups are deep golden brown.
Serve with cheese sauce, if desired.

title: sausage-potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes according to boxes and put together in one 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Add sausages and bake according to box. Let set 5 minutes to thicken and serve.

title: my italian casserole
directions: In large saucepan brown beef and onion and drain fat.
Add sauce, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepperoni and simmer about 10 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan mix noodles and sauce and mix. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until the cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot tuna teasers
directions: Flake the tuna and blend thoroughly with remaining ingredients.
Spread on crackers or Melba rounds.
Place under broiler to brown lightly. Garnish with paprika.

title: our vegetable soup
directions: Chop onions and brown with ground beef.
Add beef mixture to cooked potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until garlic mellows to desired taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with one pie pastry.
Crumble up crackers and place in pastry.

title: salmon rice casserole
directions: For cheese sauce, combine milk, cheese, salt and pepper in a double boiler.
Heat only until well blended and smooth.
Put a layer of cooked rice in a well-greased baking dish.
On top of this, arrange layers of salmon, olives and the cheese sauce. Repeat, ending with cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and onions together until tender; drain.
Add tuna, soup and milk.
Mix together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Fruit:
Peel, core and slice apples.
Puree in blender, mixing with apple juice.
Serve immediately or cook in a little boiling water 20 to 30 minutes, then puree into applesauce.
Freeze (cooked only).

title: diabetic corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, baking powder, powdered milk and flour. Alternate water and meal.
Spray a 7 x 11-inch Pyrex pan with Pam. Heat.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour corn bread in hot pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: cucumber dip with herbs and borage blossoms
directions: For Dip:
Finely chop the cucumber.
Combine cucumber with vinegar, soy sauce, Bitters and sugar.
Season with salt and pepper.
Let set.
Add garlic and herbs, toss well and add to sour cream and yogurt; combine well.
Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1 cup juice.
Arrange fruit in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine reserved juice with brown sugar, cornstarch, orange rind, cinnamon and margarine in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, cream well.
Cover vanilla wafer crumbs (reserving 1/4 of crumbs for top) with butter mixture.
Cover this with strawberries. Cover berries with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Cover with 1/4 of crumbs.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: louise's corn dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in buttered 2-quart baking dish. Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine.
Fry by tablespoons in hot oil until golden brown. Serves 8.

title: hickory holler persimmon pudding squares
directions: Mix all together, except last items (nuts, raisins and coconut), in a large bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center comes out clean.
Pudding will flatten when cooled.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave uncovered on High until thick and bubbly, stirring frequently.
Can be baked in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thick.
Tastes like fresh!

title: souper green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine green beans and mushroom soup in casserole dish.
Add and mix in 1/2 can fried dried onions. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered.
Before serving top with remainder of fried onions.

title: brown rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt.
Slowly add picked and thoroughly washed rice so that water continues to boil.
Boil rice for one minute uncovered.
Stir rice and put tight fitting lid on pot.
Simmer for 45 minutes over medium heat.
Do not remove lid until rice has cooked and saturate for 5 to 10 minutes.
Fluff up rice with a fork and serve.
Makes 3 cups.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, blend well and bake 1 hour and 12 minutes at 350°.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix together all but sour cream and nuts, then add sour cream and nuts; mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator until nice and cold.
Very easy.
Serves about 6.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple
and
save
juice.
Add
flour,
sugar, juice from pineapple
and egg in a saucepan.
Cook on low heat and stir constantly	until thick.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add Cool Whip and
mix together.	Add apples, peanuts and pineapple. Refrigerate.

title: linda's fudge pudding cake
directions: Pour cold water over the whole thing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix well.
Divide into 2 containers.
Place in refrigerator. Add 3 quarts ginger ale or Sprite to each container of punch.

title: hot fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add chocolate and boiling water and bring to boil until thickened.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread a little oleo on each tortilla and wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat in oven for 15 minutes.
Fry beef until brown.
Add onion and cook until onion is done.
Add both packages of taco sauce mix and follow directions on back.

title: baby manapua
directions: Chop Charsui and green onion fine.
Add ajinomoto and pepper. Put just enough shoyu to moisten meat.
Flatten biscuit dough; put a teaspoon of meat in the center.
Fold all four sides of dough (pinch closed).
Steam or bake it.
If you steam it, put wax paper under each manapua and a fingertip of oil on top of manapua.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Measure first 5 ingredients into bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan. Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Set in refrigerator for about 30 minutes to 1 hour to chill dough.
Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° for about 7 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese-stuffed meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, onion, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and one can of tomato sauce.
Pat half of mixture into loaf pan.
Place cheese down center and cover with remaining meat, pressing edges of meat together.
Top with the second can of tomato sauce and bake 1 hour or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Into large bowl measure all ingredients except chocolate pieces and nuts.
With mixer at medium speed, beat until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Stir in chocolate and nuts. Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
With pancake turner, remove cookies to wire racks; cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: quick pizza fix
directions: Brown ground beef; add pizza sauce and heat thoroughly. Split muffins.
Spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons of the sauce over each split muffin.
Add
any or all of the other ingredients.	Top with Mozzarella	cheese.
Put
under
the broiler on a cookie sheet for
minutes,
or
until
the
cheese is browned and bubbly. Kids love to make and to eat these.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° for 15 minutes while beating egg whites. Mix eggs, salt and cream of tartar until stiff (10 to 15 minutes). Add sugar gradually.
Beat well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Put 2 layers of wax paper on cookie sheet.
Drop cookies onto sheet by teaspoon.
Turn off oven and put cookies in.
Leave overnight. Keep in airtight container.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, Equal and cooking oil.
Blend in flour and soda. Add cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla and bananas.
Pour into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: cheese grits
directions: Heat milk and butter in deep saucepan to boiling point but do not boil.
Add grits and cook 15 minutes or until done, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add salt and pepper.
Beat vigorously (electric beater at high) for 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole and pour melted butter over top. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake about 30 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Saute chicken in hot oil until lightly brown.
Drain.
Stir in soup, milk, mustard and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Bring to a full boil, then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix Bisquick flour and shredded cheese together until well blended.
Add sausage to mixture; mix well.
Make teaspoon size balls.
Place them on an ungreased sheet pan.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Soak with paper towels, then serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate onion and pepper in a colander and strain out some of the juice.
While this strains, grate the Colby cheese and let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese, Colby cheese, onion, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll in a ball or 2 logs and roll in crushed pecans or sprinkle with paprika.

title: raw apple nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and combine with creamed mixture.
Add apples.
Spread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix the graham crackers, powdered sugar and peanut butter and refrigerate for 1 hour. Form into walnut size balls in palm of your hand. Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Do not melt chocolate too far in advance and dip soon after the chocolate is melted. Dip balls in dipping chocolate and then place onto waxed paper.
A two prong fork works well for dipping.

title: broccoli-pasta soup
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic.
Boil 4 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Season with pepper.
Freezes well.

title: flop cake
directions: Blend all ingredients with a spoon.
Do not beat.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: meltaways
directions: Combine cottage cheese and 1 cup butter in large mixer bowl; mix thoroughly.
Add flour gradually, beating until dough forms a ball.
Divide in thirds; wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Roll each piece into a 9-inch circle.

title: grandpa joe's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash chicken thoroughly (inside and out).
Mix oil, vinegar, salt, paprika and black pepper in a small bowl.
Pour mixture inside and over chicken and massage into meat. Let excess remain in bottom of baking dish.
Stuff chicken with apple, orange, onion and celery (as full as possible).
Sprinkle paprika and parsley flakes on top of garnishment.
Cook in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Reduce heat to 325° (lay sheet of tinfoil on top to prevent from burning) and continue cooking for 45 minutes (longer if chicken is very large).

title: sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Cut the tomatoes lengthwise, leaving them attached at the bottom end and open them like a book.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream sugar and Crisco. Add 1 egg at a time; beat.
Add milk and dry ingredients, alternating.
Beat well.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Cook on low, 300°, for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.

title: sour cream and cheese hashbrowns
directions: Take potatoes out of freezer 1 hour before mixing.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, mix ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: no-fuss curry chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
In oblong 3-quart baking dish (13 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inches), stir together onion, apple, tomatoes, salt and curry powder.
Top with chicken, skin side up, in a single layer.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven until chicken is tender and skin crisp, about 1 hour.

title: salad dressing
directions: Microwave 4 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon cornstarch moistened with milk.
Microwave 2 1/4 minutes. Beat, if not smooth.
This is a good dressing for waldorf or potato salad, also cole slaw.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash potatoes.
Pour the first 5 ingredients in baking dish and top with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Even better if you put sliced, drained pineapple in baking dish before putting in potato mixture.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: In clear 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, bake cake according to directions on the box.
Let cool.
Spread pineapple over cake. Prepare instant pudding according to box.
Spread pudding over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Top with cherries and pecans.
Very nice for family get togethers.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix until moist by hand.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° until 3/4 done (maybe 25 minutes).
Brown on top.
Pour topping over cake. Finish baking (maybe 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: dip mix
directions: Mix until smooth and chill.

title: banana peppers
directions: Beat egg yellow; add beer and mix well.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add to beer mixture.
Beat egg white.
Fold into other mixture.
Add oil.
Dip peppers; fry.

title: chruty ky(bow ties)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Beat egg yolks until pale yellow.
Add with remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture; stir until well blended, then knead until mixture forms one large ball.
Roll out on well floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into strips 1 x 3-inch.
Make slit in center; put one end through slit.
Fry in oil at 375° until light brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: country ham - avocado balls
directions: Combine ham and grated avocado (skin removed).
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Makes about 75.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain and wash noodles with cold water.
Start to add any kind of vegetables that you want in salad.
Use a lot of salad dressing to make it wet, then add a lot of Salad Supreme seasoning to flavor.
Put in refrigerator.

title: snow ball cake
directions: Bake cake in 10 x 14-inch pan.
When cake is done, remove from oven and punch 5 holes in top with wooden spoon.
Then spread pineapple over cake.
Layer pudding on top of pineapple.
Spread sliced bananas over pudding.
Beat Cool Whip and sour cream together.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over cake.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti 15 minutes; drain.
Rinse with cool water; drain well.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
You may need to add more Italian salad oil before serving if too dry.

title: broiled pesto tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half lengthwise.
Place tomatoes on oven-safe dish with cut side of tomatoes up.
Spread 1/2 teaspoon of pesto onto each cut piece of tomato.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas pecan cake
directions: Soak pecans overnight in lemon extract.
Preheat oven to 300°. Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add fruit and nuts and stir.
Spoon into pan, slightly flattening top.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Delicious, much better than fruit cake.

title: souper meat'n potatoes pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate or 9 x 9-inch square Pyrex dish.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix
salt,
flour,
sugar, soda, eggs and fruit cocktail well, pour
into greased pan.
Top with brown sugar and pecans. Sprinkle over raw dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: best ever chicken and dumplings
directions: *Add more water, if too much boils away.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place a layer of the meat, Tater Tots, cheese and 1/2 of the soup.
Repeat layers.
Cook 30 minutes covered and 30 more minutes uncovered.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: olga's german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter on 9-inch ovenproof skillet.
Mix eggs, flour and milk together with a fork.
(Batter should be lumpy.)
Pour into skillet and bake in hot (425°) oven about 20 minutes until puffy and golden brown.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Return to oven briefly. Sprinkle with lemon juice and serve immediately.
Cut into wedges with kitchen shears.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: In a big pot, place a cut up chicken and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Let boil until tender and golden and fat rises to top of the water, making a rich broth.
Add a batch of Rolled Out Pastry.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine first 5 ingredients together in a bowl.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix only until all ingredients are well combined.
Put into a well greased 8-inch by 8-inch pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: bread dressing
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Make in 3 layers.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening
and
sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating
after each addition.
Add flour which has been sifted with
baking
powder,
alternately
with milk, beginning with flour, then milk
and
ending with flour. Add vanilla and almond extract;
mix
well.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: pastor dave's absolute favorite banana yeast bread(from "a diary of bread")
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and ginger.
In saucepan, heat milk, 1/2 cup sugar, butter or margarine and salt until warm and butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add to dry mixture; add banana, 1 egg and 1 egg yolk. (Reserve white).
Stir well.
Add flour gradually and blend to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead 5 to 8 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl; let rise until double.
Punch down; divide into 2 parts.
Shape in 2 round loaves; place on baking sheet.
Make slashes about 1/4-inch deep around loaf every 3/4 inch like a sunburst.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: lipton onion rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on medium setting until water evaporates (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).
Stir and serve.

title: gratin potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes slices in buttered 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Stir together cream and remaining ingredients; pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender and mixture is bubbly and golden.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hamburger slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and use on your favorite hamburger.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
When preparing quick bread according to loaf instructions, substitute applesauce for oil required. Substitute 1/4 cup egg substitute for the egg in recipe.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate swirl coffee cake
directions: Use an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Stir together the coconut, nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon melted margarine; set aside. Mix the Bisquick, 1/4 cup sugar, remaining melted butter, the egg and milk.
Pour into pan.
Spoon chocolate over batter and with knife cut through batter (marble effect).
Sprinkle coconut mixture on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: "killer" casserole
directions: Layer hamburger meat, potatoes and cheese; repeat layers, if desired.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top melts.
(Potatoes may be leftovers or fresh.)

title: hot dish
directions: Combine all.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Top with lots of buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add salsa, picante sauce, seasoning and tomatoes.
Simmer for 30 minutes on low.
Then add 16 ounces Velveeta cheese (cubed).
Stir to make sure cheese does not stick or burn.
Put in crock-pot.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling or fresh fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients
with water and poppy seeds.
Beat and then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Mix dressing and other ingredients. Cool macaroni and mix all together.
Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; spread flat into two rectangles and press seams together.
Beat cream cheese and salad dressing mix until blended.
Spread cheese on rectangle.
Roll up jellyroll style and wrap tightly.
Chill until firm; slice thinly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: bubble stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Have fun blowing bubbles!

title: cheesy sausage or hamburger quiche
directions: Fry sausage and drain, reserving 2 tablespoons fat. Saute onion and green pepper in fat. Combine cheese and flour. Stir in sausage and remaining ingredients and spread in pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: roast
directions: Put roast in crock-pot and top with dry onion soup mix. Spread the soup over the onion mixture and slowly pour Pepsi over. Cook until done. Makes its own gravy.

title: lemon-sponge pie
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 420° for 15 minutes; lower oven to 325°.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Test with a knife.

title: braised brisket of beef
directions: Melt the shortening in a Dutch oven and saute the onion and garlic, being careful not to burn the garlic.
When the onion is translucent, transfer onion and garlic to a dish and save.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with margarine. Place potatoes in pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with onions and chicken soup.
Spread sour cream over mixture and then top with cheese.
Sprinkle the corn flakes over the top and pour the melted margarine over the entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: duck soup
directions: Place all in a large pot.
Simmer gently for 2 or 3 hours. If too thick, add 1 cup water.
Add 2 or 3 ounces of thin noodles. Cook very slowly 1/2 hour longer and serve.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine string beans, peas, butter beans, pimiento, celery and onion in bowl.
Combine vinegar, salt and salad oil and shake in jar to mix.
Pour over vegetables and leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: hobbs cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
In mixing bowl, add all dry ingredients together; mix thoroughly.
Make a well in the middle of mixing bowl; pour milk in the center of the well. Slowly mix dry ingredients with milk until all are blended until smooth.
Add to melted butter in baking dish.
Add fruit; no need to stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir in butter, Parmesan and egg. Form into crust of pie pan or casserole dish.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti.
In skillet, cook ground beef, onion and pepper until done; drain.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, paste, sugar, oregano and salt; heat.
Pour over cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bottom of pan. Stir all ingredients with a fork until moistened. Beat vigorously for 1 minute. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes clean, 55 to 65 minutes.

title: beef-n-biscuit
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, then drain. In mixing bowl, combine tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Add beef mixture to bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Set aside.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Mix ingredients together several hours before serving. Refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart relish.

title: roast(pot or oven)
directions: Brown roast in hot fat (2 tablespoons vegetable oil) in heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
In separate pan, heat water, salt, pepper, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring almost to boil.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for about 3 hours.
Sometimes after browning, I place meat in small roaster pan, pour liquid mixture over meat and place in preheated oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with water.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Mix well.
Stir a few pecans at a time into the mixture, until all nuts are coated.
Spread nuts in a single layer on greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for about 45 minutes or until golden.
(Clean and grease baking sheets between batches.)
Let cool.
Break apart, if
necessary.
Store cool nuts in an airtight container or plastic bag.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt, then beat into egg mixture; add vanilla. Fold in apples, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab stuffed chicken breast
directions: Mix bread crumbs with pepper, paprika, parsley and oil.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: fullabull's coconut sheath cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Let cool.
Punch holes in top of cake and pour one can of Eagle Brand milk over it.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Pour into greased rectangular pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lamb curry
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, crumble lamb.
Add celery, onion and garlic.
Micro-cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 5 to 7 minutes or until no pink remains and celery and onion are tender, stirring once.
Drain off fat.
Stir in flour, curry powder, bouillon granules and pepper.
Then stir in apple, water, milk and raisins.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: south african gourmet salad
directions: Drop frozen rock lobster tails into boiling salted water.
When water re-boils, cook for 3 minutes.
Drain immediately; drench with cold water and cut away underside membrane.
Remove meat from shells.
Chill.
Boil potatoes; drain and peel.
While still warm, cut into cubes in bottom of large bowl.
Add onion, salt and pepper immediately.
Mix mayonnaise with cream until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and onions and leave in a thick top layer.
Cool, then chill.
At serving time, cut chilled rock lobster meat into bite size pieces.
Add to potatoes in bowl and toss together until all ingredients are well blended.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: perfect chocolate cake(may prepare ahead.  makes one 3-layer cake.)
directions: Combine cocoa and boiling water, stirring until smooth; set aside to cool.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Combine dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with cocoa mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Do not overbeat!
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out of the center clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove and cool completely.

title: oven rice dressing
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Combine with other ingredients and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with foil and cook at 400° for 1 hour.

title: spinach stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degree.
Cut 1/2 inch slice from top of each tomato; scoop out pulp, leaving shell intact.
Fill each tomato with spinach souffl; sprinkle cheese over top.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: spoon bread muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in greased muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Lay pecans on foil-lined pan. Cover with 3 tablespoons melted butter or margarine. Salt to taste. Put in 325° oven for 15 minutes. Turn off heat and leave in oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours with door closed.

title: icing - cream cheese
directions: Ice cake while warm.

title: mom's potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half.
Then cut into even wedges.
Boil potato wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with butter, spices and herbs. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve as a snack or with any meat.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter and nuts together.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: "mike riley's" chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greetings and smiles thoroughly.
Add handshake separately.
Slowly stir in love.
Sift sympathy and hospitality and fold in carefully.
Bake in warm heart.
Serve often.

title: crab stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and add wine, crabmeat and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle each breast with salt and pepper.
Divide stuffing among breasts and roll.
Secure with toothpicks.
Coat each breast with flour mixed with paprika.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer; gradually add brown sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, molasses, and lemon juice; beat well.
Combine 2 cups flour and next 7 ingredients; stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture; mix well. Gradually add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough, mixing well.
Shape dough into a ball.
Cover, chill at least 1 hour.

title: pear honey
directions: Grate pears.
Boil all ingredients for 20 minutes. Refrigerate.

title: slow-cooked mac `n' cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Place in a 5-quart slow cooker; add butter. In a bowl, combine the eggs, evaporated milk, soup, milk and 3 cups cheese. Pour over macaroni mixture; stir to combine. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Cook 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with paprika. Yield: 10 servings.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and jello.
Then mix with eggs, oil and water.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix first 6 ingredients with 1/2 can Manwich sauce. Shape into a loaf in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain excess fat; spread mustard over the top of the loaf.
Pour on remaining Manwich.
Bake 35 minutes longer.

title: oven brisket
directions: Sprinkle both sides of brisket with liberal amounts of salts and peppers to taste.
Bake, fat side up, in a shallow pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour apple cider vinegar over meat.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours more.
As juices bake away, add water to bottom of pan and more vinegar over meat.
Add more water to drippings when finished to make gravy.
Best cooked ahead, sliced across the grain and reheated in drippings later.
Gets better every time reheated.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mimi's crumb cake
directions: Cream the shortening, butter or margarine, and sugar; add flour and pecans.
Set aside 1/2 of this mixture.
To remaining half, add egg, vanilla, sour cream, and baking soda.
Mix well. Place in 9 x 13 sheet cake pan.
Top with reserved dry mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup margarine. Press into bottom and sides of a large pie plate.
Beat the confectioners sugar, eggs, 2 sticks margarine and vanilla with electric beater for 20 minutes.
Pour mixture into crust.
Spread the well drained pineapple on top of the cream mixture.
Place the cut bananas on top of pineapple; place close together.
Spread the Cool Whip on the bananas.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chopped cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: coffee punch
directions: Early in the day or on the day before, make coffee and refrigerate until chilled.
Very strong chicory or Italian grind coffee is best.
Just before serving, whip cream, adding sugar and vanilla.
Add whipped cream.
Pour cold coffee over it and mix well.
Serve in cups.
Yield: 50 to 60 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine the oleo, sugar, sour cream, flour, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Put half in tube pan. Sprinkle with a mixture of the brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Add other half of the mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt laura's green beans
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute onion until translucent. Add flour, spices and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer until thickened. In a 1 1/2-quart, covered, casserole layer: 1 can of beans, half tomato mixture, second can of beans and remainder of tomato mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove lid, brown under broiler and serve.

title: salad for all seasons
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Store in icebox until ready to serve.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Chop each vegetable in chopper or blender.
Drain off liquid and discard.
Mix all vegetables with salt and let stand overnight, covered.
The next morning, drain liquid again.
Place vinegar, sugar and spice in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Spoon vegetable mix into sterile jars.
Cover with pickling solution. Seal at once and process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Jars should seal as they cool.
This is a sweet relish.
Good on hot dogs, etc.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Place oil in pan; add onions.
Cook slow.
Do not brown.
Add tomatoes, pepper, mushrooms, celery and salt.
Cook for 1 hour very slowly, then add peas.
In a large roaster place layer of spaghetti, chicken, cheese and sauce, repeating until all is used. Heat in oven 20 minutes.
Serves 25.

title: chicken with greek citrus marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid. Shake well.

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Beat in currant jelly and stir to thaw and break apart frozen raspberries.
This will start the gelatin to congeal.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch salad pan.
Chill. Top with whipped topping.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy and add eggs.
Mix until blended and add flour, salt, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wayne's easy pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternately add flour and milk.
Add vanilla extract.
Pour batter into tube pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Beat egg.
Mix with ground meat, crackers and salt.
Make into small balls, about the size of a walnut.
Brown little in Crisco. Put balls in casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over meat balls and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, turning frequently.
Make sauce.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Drain drippings from ribs; remove rack and pour sauce over ribs.
Bake 45 minutes, basting frequently.
Serve with rice.

title: fish supreme
directions: Place fish in baking pan with butter.
Pour in milk to cover fish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.

title: banana oatmeal nutbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, bananas, honey and eggs.
Sift together salt, flour, spices, baking powder and soda and stir into banana mixture.
Blend in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fresh stewed corn
directions: Shuck the corn and remove the silks.
Wash the corn and dry it with paper towels.
Place the ears directly on the middle oven rack.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn oven to broil and turn corn to brown all over, cooking about 15 minutes more.
Serve with butter.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Boil potato in a large pot until tender.
Set aside.
Make white sauce.
Mix flour, oleo, half and half and cheese together; cook until thickened, stirring continually.
Then you may add the bacon, green onion and celery to the potato mixture and white sauce.
Add salt to taste.
Cheese and bouillon are salty, so add salt according to taste.
Serves 8.

title: italian sausage and onion
directions: Brown sausages; add water.
Cover and let steam 1/2 hour; drain.
Brown again.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook onions and pepper in oil until tender.
Add sausages with the white wine and heat through.
You can serve this over pasta.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. Place broccoli in casserole over chicken.
Dilute soup with water. Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Pour over chicken and broccoli; top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: breakfast punch
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1/4 up to 1 cup sugar (according to how sweet it is or how sweet you want it).
Put in freezer and freeze. Take out about 2 hours before serving time.
Serve slushy.
Add 1 quart ginger ale an hour before serving.
Serves 30.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Cream margarine, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add corn flakes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: marshmallow meringue
directions: Beat 3 egg whites and a dash of salt until frothy.
Add 1 cup Kraft Marshmallow.	Continue
to
beat until stiff peaks are formed.
Spread over
pie
filling.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: jack's apple pie
directions: Butter pie pan.
Make crust thin as you can work with and press into pan.
Coat inside of crust with cream.
Stir apples (peeled, cored and sliced thin) with sugar and cinnamon.
Spread evenly in pan.
Cross top of apples with 1/2-inch wide strips of dough, every 1-inch.
Cross strips from opposite directions.
Brush top of pie with butter lightly and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Place in oven at approximately 375° until crust is brown.

title: ham rolls
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on 1 slice of ham.
Roll it up. Slice into 5 sections.
Insert toothpicks.
Serve.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl. Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk.
Mix gently.
Knead lightly on floured surface (handle as little as possible).
Roll out dough to 1-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter. Place in pan and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk gradually.
Cover and let stand 1/2 hour.
Preheat oven to 425° (this is the secret to success).
Muffin tins should be greased and very hot prior to placing batter in them.
Only pour about 1/2 inch into each tin. Cook approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
It should rise and brown. If taken out too early, it will be soggy.
If oven and tin are not hot enough, it won't brown.
Normally served with roast beef, potatoes and gravy.

title: coconut apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Peel, core and slice apples.
Cut apples in half.
Combine apple slices, topping and flour in bowl. Spoon into a pie pan. Peel apart each biscuit into two thinner biscuits and place on top of apples. Drizzle butter over biscuits.
Combine sugar and coconut.
Sprinkle over biscuits and bake 30 minutes.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy Dutch oven.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Pour chicken mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with Pastry.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: pudding dirt cups
directions: Crush the cookies; set aside.
Pour milk in bowl, add pudding and beat until blended.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of the cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies in cup.
Fill 3/4 full with pudding mix.
Top with cookies (crushed).
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Decorate with gummy worms, gummy bugs and candy flowers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve pudding, 2 cups pineapple, peach and apricot juice. Add drained pineapple, drained peaches (cut fine), drained apricots (cut fine) and sliced bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Mix in a bowl chicken soup, mayonnaise and chicken seasoning. In a different bowl, put broccoli, then chicken, then mixture, then cheese, then stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deluxe chicken and rice
directions: In roasting pan, place rice and Cup-a-Soup and mix dry.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture; add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on chicken.
Add water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.

title: chilli dogs
directions: Will need 2 saucepans, a cheese grater and frying pan.

title: cheese log #2
directions: Blend cheese well in mixer.
Add onions, 1/3 cup of nuts and sour cream. Chill until firm.
Shape into a log.
Spread chopped nuts on waxed paper and coat the cheese log by rolling it on the nuts. Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Simmer all together for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium-sized bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in bowl.
To assemble, spread bean dip on a large platter.
Top with avocado mixture; layer with sour cream-taco mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and gelatin powder in a large bowl.
Beat in oil, eggs, water, and strawberries.
Pour into two 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost with strawberry icing.

title: sweet sauerkraut
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar until the sugar melts.
Combine green pepper, onion, celery, pimento and sauerkraut.
Pour vinegar and sugar mixture over the sauerkraut.
Mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken salsa pizza
directions: Place bread shell on an ungreased 12 inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese.
Top with salsa, chicken, and remaining cheese.
Bake at 450° for 8 - 10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan lightly with cooking spray.

title: light crab spread
directions: Finely chop onion; press garlic and mix onion, garlic, cheese and milk until well blended.
Spread in shallow serving dish. Coarsely chop tomato, green pepper and parsley.
Mix together tomato, green pepper, 2 tablespoons parsley, lemon juice and salt. Spoon on top of cheese mixture.
Top with crab meat.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Chill.
Serve with bread or veggies.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Coat grill rack with vegetable spray.

Place chicken on rack over medium hot coals and cook 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently with soy mixture. Transfer chicken to warm serving platter; garnish with thin green onion strips, if desired.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: In saucepan cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender. In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup and sour cream.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot. Stir.
Sprinkle with additional paprika.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, vanilla and margarine. It will make a mixture similar to cookie dough. Roll into balls. Then melt chocolate.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin wax using a double boiler. Dip chocolate balls into chocolate, coating entire ball. Place on wax paper.

title: raisin banana muffins
directions: Spray a 12-muffin pan with cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put bananas into a blender; blend until smooth.
Scrape bananas into a mixing bowl and combine with egg and oil.
In another bowl, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add banana mixture to the dry ingredients and blend.
Stir in the raisins.
Spoon 1/3 cup of batter into 10 to 12 muffin cups.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken
directions: Place cooked chicken and broccoli in 9 X 13 baking pan.
Blend both soups and mayonnaise together; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with Mazzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until heated through.

title: lemon cream dip with fresh fruit
directions: Beat together cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and lemon juice.
Chill to blend flavors. Serve with assortment of fresh fruit.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat egg with fork.
Beat in buttermilk or sour milk and oil.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until blended but still slightly lumpy.
Lightly grease a griddle or heavy skillet.
Heat until water sprinkled on griddle dances across surface.
Pour about 1/4 cup batter on griddle for each pancake.
When pancakes have a bubbly surface and slightly dry edges, turn to cook other side. Leftover batter may be refrigerated.
Makes 8 to 9 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: tarragon chicken
directions: On
wax
paper, mix flour, salt, tarragon
and	pepper. Place tarragon vinegar in shallow dish.
Roll each
piece
of chicken in vinegar, then dust lightly with flour
mixture.
In large, nonstick frypan, place olive oil and heat
over
medium temperature.
Add	chicken and cook 10 minutes on	each
side until
brown.
Pour
remaining vinegar over
chicken.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, turning until chicken is
done.
Cover while cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried cheese sticks
directions: Cut cheese crosswise into 3/4-inch slices.
Lay slices flat and cut in half lengthwise.
Combine flour and red pepper; stir well. Dip cheese sticks in beaten eggs.
Dredge in flour mixture.
Dip coated cheese in egg again; dredge in breadcrumbs, pressing firmly so that crumbs adhere.
Place cheese sticks on a wax paper lined baking sheet and freeze for at least 30 minutes.
Fry in deep hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve immediately with favorite sauce.
(Mozzarella, Swiss or plain Monterey Jack cheese may also be used.)

title: swedish creme
directions: Note:
This dessert must be made a day ahead of serving time.

title: noel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in fruits and nuts. Pour 1/2
mixture
in 12 x 8-inch dish; chill and set.
Spread sour cream
on
set
mixture
and
add rest of Jell-O mixture. Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: nacho platter
directions: Line bottom of pan with lettuce.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread over lettuce.
Add tomatoes, Cheddar and olives.
Pour taco sauce on top.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook together until thick (not very long).
Remove from stove and add 3 large tablespoons strawberry jello.
Add 1 quart fresh strawberries (well drained) to cornstarch mixture.
Pour into baked, cooled crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Fill crock-pot with quartered apples (peelings too).
Add 3 1/2 cups sugar (use 2 1/2 cups for sweet apples) and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Let stand overnight.
Do not lift lid.
Next morning, cook on high for 4 hours.
Blend cooked apple mixture in blender until smooth.
Serve on warm biscuits.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Take rolls or biscuits and roll 1/4 inch.
Spread with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll and cut 1/2-inch thick.
Place in buttered round cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken curry bombay
directions: In skillet, cook onion, garlic and curry powder in oil until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chicken, tomatoes and raisins; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes.
Add new potatoes and green beans.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serves 4.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.
Cooking time: 18 minutes.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Boil the noodles in 2-quart saucepan. Do not cook fully. Without draining noodles, add bouillon cubes and cubed beef towards end of cooking noodles.
Cook on low for a few minutes. Top with butter before serving.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together in a casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
A great side dish with chicken, beef, fish or pork.

title: not so sweet punch
directions: Mix and add ice.
Can be served with most anything.

title: scott's dip
directions: In a mixing bowl combine cream cheese and sour cream. Mix until smooth. Spread in a nine by thirteen inch pan. Sprinkle that with garlic salt. Cover the mixture with a layer of picante sauce. Add tomatoes and onions. Then top with the rest of picante and sprinkle with cheese.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix above ingredients well, pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry shell and bake in a 350° oven for 45 - 50 minutes.

title: dee's frozen punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar.
Add 1 quart boiling water and mix well. Add cold water and lemon and pineapple juices.
Pour into gallon plastic container and freeze.
When ready to serve, allow to sit at room temperature 3 to 6 hours, depending on temperature.
Let thaw partially until mushy.
Add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Serves 40 punch cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer and serve.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Slice cooked potatoes thinly.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and add cheese.
Mix well and turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Mix together and heat vegetables.
Then add sugar, vinegar, cooking oil and paprika.
Stir well and let stand at least overnight.
This improves with age.
I find LeSueur peas are best. I also find it is better if made 4 or 5 days in advance.
I've never seen it spoil.
Is delicious with cornbread dressing.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add soup from the can.
Add flour and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 325°.

title: spicy apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Arrange apples in pie plate with crust. Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over the apples.
Add the crust (top).
Bake for 45 minutes or until the apples are tender.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, then add mayonnaise and water. Mix only enough for a smooth batter.
Do not beat.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool.
Frost with peanut butter frosting.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add egg; mix until well blended. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
