Press remainder evenly on bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: carol's cranberry ambrosia
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts. Gently fold in Cool Whip and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: aunt esther's date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates, soda and shortening; set aside.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift cake flour 3 times.
Sift sugar 1 time.
Mix sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, mixing in one at a time.
Add half of flour and mix again.
Pour in Seven-Up and lemon flavoring; mix in remaining flour.
Bake 90 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Melt butter in pan, making sure butter coats sides of pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in Jell-O and beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, oranges, pineapple, soda and pecans.
Chill until mixture thickens.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
16 to 20 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl stir spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions until well mixed. Cover, chill 2 hours to blend flavors. Stir well. If desired, spoon into round bread bowl. Serve with cut-up vegetables, chips, or crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over gelatin in a medium bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill overnight or until set.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: glorified brownies
directions: Cream sugar, 1/2 cup butter or oleo and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and 3 tablespoons cocoa together.
Add to egg mixture.
Put in pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese-n-chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in 1 cup cheese.

title: old fashioned nut loaf
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening until soft and smooth.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until fluffy.
Add vanilla, then beat in thoroughly 1 egg at a time. Add nuts; beat well.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: col. sanders style chicken
directions: Mix all spices.
This is enough to coat 4 chickens.
For one fryer meal, add 3 tablespoons mix to flour and brown sugar.
Shake all ingredients in a bag.
Arrange the coated chicken in an oven bag.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350° without turning.

title: broiled crab sandwiches
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread.
Spread mixture on slices.
Place on cookie sheets and broil until bubbly and brown.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Dilute spaghetti sauce with 10 ounces water.
Simmer in pan over low heat.
Cover bottom of large baking dish with spaghetti sauce.
Layer filled shells and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Cover dish and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover; sprinkle with grated Mozzarella cheese; bake 10 minutes more. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 20 minutes, or until thick, fudge consistency. Cool completely. Place cookies in a food processor and process until it resembles dirt. Mix the cookies and margarine and press into a well greased 9 x 13 inch pan and freeze. Spread softened ice cream over frozen cookie crumb crust. Freeze.

title: prayer bars
directions: Blend 1/3 cup butter, cocoa, sugar and egg together.
Heat until mixture thickens.
Add crushed crackers, coconut, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spread mixture in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Chill until hard.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add bananas, pecans and milk.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas (1 to a pie) to cover bottom of baked pie shells.
Soften cream cheese to room temperature and cream with sugar.
Prepare whipped topping mix according to package directions.
Blend together with cream cheese mixture.
Put in pie shells.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill and keep refrigerated.

title: laredo supper
directions: Saute chopped onion; add ground meat. Brown and drain. Add Cheez Whiz and spices, tomato sauce and undrained beans. Simmer 30 minutes. Serve over crushed Fritos.

title: fruit antipasto
directions: Remove rind from melon.
Snip grapes into small bunches.
Cut cheese into 1-inch cubes.
Arrange wedges of lemon on tray, tuck cheese between wedges.
Ring with grapes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Add Cool Whip and Grape-Nuts. Put in refrigerator to thicken.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Slice zucchini into thin slices.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: feathery fudge cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans. Combine the first 3 ingredients.
In a mixer bowl, beat butter on medium speed of electric mixer, about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat until well combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Blend in cooled chocolate.
Add dry ingredients and cold water alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Turn into pan.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks. Remove from pans.
Cool.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corned beef stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers; cook peppers in boiling water until almost tender or about 5 minutes; drain.
Mix corned beef and next 4 ingredients.
Fill peppers, top with buttered bread crumbs.
Put tin foil around the bottom of peppers and put in a baking dish with a little water.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in pan; pour mixture into large bowl and stir in powdered sugar. Mix graham cracker crumbs into mixture; place mixture into flat pan about 3/4-inch thick! Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture, then cut into squares before cooling.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together (in large mixing bowl), all ingredients.
Put into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until
crisp and drain most of the bacon fat. Add green pepper, celery and mushrooms.
Saute until transparent.
Add rice, chicken and soy sauce.
"Enjoy."

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except peanuts and apples in Small Batter Bowl; mix well. Chop peanuts using Food Chopper; add to Batter Bowl. Mix well; chill. Wedge apples using Apple Wedger; arrange around dip and serve. Yield: 16 servings (2 cups).

title: diet orange frosty
directions: Mix well in blender.
Pour into frosty glass.
Add your straw, sit back with your feet up and cool off.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, then add oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Grease 2 loaf pans and flour lightly.
Bake on lowest rack.
Set oven at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool.

title: lemon cake
directions: Fold above together until moist.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in greased and floured 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until sugar has dissolved. Place in container of ice cream freezer and process as directed.

title: tomato kraut
directions: Mix all ingredients together, including all the juice, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, until juices cook out and the top is browning.
Sugar and bacon fat can be reduced by half.

title: ten ingredients fried rice
directions: Cook the rice the night before and store in the refrigerator. Heat wok until hot.
Add 1 tablespoon oil and beaten eggs.
Remove; set aside.
Heat the rest of the oil and fry onions until transparent.
Add shrimp and meats.
Stir until meat is cooked. Add vegetables.
Add the rice and stir-fry.
Mix the water, soy sauce and pepper.
Add to rice.
Continue stirring.
Add the scrambled eggs and continue to stir-fry.
Add more soy sauce for color if needed.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: new england apple cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add next 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Spoon into greased 10-inch Bundt or tube pan (I use a 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out almost clean.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes; turn onto serving dish.
When completely cooled, dust with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Bake at 350°.

title: quick and delicious rolls
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into 12 cup muffin pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown at 450°.

title: aunt mae's pecan cookies
directions: Beat egg white until very stiff.
Add sugar and flour and beat.
Stir in pecans.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake for 30 minutes at 275°.

title: banana cake(by mrs. edmund g. brown, former first lady of california)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together; set aside. Cream butter with extract; gradually add fructose, creaming thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sieve bananas and mix with buttermilk.

Beating only until smooth after each addition, mix the creamed butter extract, 1/4 dry ingredients and 1/3 of the banana mixture; repeat 1/4 dry and 1/3 banana until all is mixed, then stir in optional walnuts. Fold in the beaten egg whites gently into the batter until thoroughly blended.
Turn batter into 2 prepared (vegetable grease and flour) pans; spread evenly to edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire racks and frost with a buttercream frosting (I don't frost; after cooling I place in the refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight, it's best served cold).

title: george strait's carne guisada
directions: Melt butter in skillet and cook meat, turning occasionally, until brown.
Add onion and bell peppers.
Add flour and let flour brown while stirring.
Mash garlic, cumin, black pepper and tomatoes.
Pour over meat and let simmer for 20 minutes, adding water if necessary, for desired thickness.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make crumb mix.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remaining mix into bottom of 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly. Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, eggs, spices and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over baked crust. Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake an additional 35 minutes. Cool before cutting into bars.
Makes 32 (1 x 2-inch) bar cookies.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet, add taco seasoning and simmer per directions on package.
Set aside.
Pour medium jar of salsa in bottom of 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Add the following to each tortilla:
1 teaspoon refried beans, spread down center. Place 1/3 slice of cheese and 1 heaping tablespoonful of taco seasoned meat.
Roll tightly with open side down.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Pour large salsa over tortillas. Sprinkle taco seasoned shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is heated through, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple spinach salad
directions: In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the oil, lemon juice, green onion, sugar, mint, salt and pepper; shake well. In a salad bowl, combine the spinach, apples and cucumber. Drizzle with dressing; toss to coat. Sprinkle with sunflower kernels.

title: passover macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar 2 or 3 tablespoons at a time until egg whites form firm peaks.
Grind or chop almonds very fine, then fold together all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto oiled baking sheet.
Flatten slightly with spoon or knife.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned and firm.
Let cool slightly, lift off baking sheet with spatula and finish cooling on wire rack.
Yields about 6 dozen small macaroons.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini and onion.
Boil for 5 minutes; drain. Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrot.
Fold in zucchini and onion.
Combine stuffing mix with butter.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top and sprinkle with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushrooms

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Add softened cream cheese and tomatoes; mix well. Pour into dish and cook in oven until bubbles.

title: cavatini
directions: Boil noodles until tender and drain.
Cook and crumble hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Combine hamburger, noodles, pepperoni, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish and add Ragu sauce.
Stir.
Top with the cheese and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cretons
directions: Cook pork and grind meat in meat grinder with onions.
Mix spices and cook over low heat until well done.
Stir often.

title: make your own onion soup mix
directions: Mix together. Store in plastic bag or covered jar in dry place.
One-half cup equals 1 package store bought mix.

title: melt-away cookies
directions: Cream butter and sifted powdered sugar together.
Add sifted flour and cornstarch and mix well.
Add a few drops of milk as needed.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully!
Cool.

title: dave's "no guilt" soup
directions: In
a
large pot, heat canned tomatoes.
Add spices and chopped
onions.
Simmer
minutes.
Add cooked vegetables, mushrooms
and
cooked
chicken
that
has been cut into small pieces.
Add
enough
water
to reach the desired consistency; less
for a thick soup, more for a thinner soup.
Add macaroni and simmer
until
the
macaroni is tender.
Adjust spices to suit your taste.
Serves 8 to 10.
A cup of soup is less than 100 calories and only 10% fat.

title: simple pancake
directions: Beat all ingredients in bowl until well blended.
Pour into preheated 450° skillet from preheated 450° oven.
Bake in oven for a few minutes.
Watch so it won't burn!
Fill the pancake with anything you want, from fruit to stir-fry vegetables.

title: pecan pie(recipe for 2 pies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add syrup, well beaten eggs, salt and vanilla.
When well mixed, add coarsely chopped pecans.
Turn into pie plates lined with pastry.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for about 1/2 to 1 hour, or until firm.

title: pineapple onion salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in pineapple juice.
Add boiling water, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into 6 individual gelatin molds or a 1-quart mold.
Chill.
Unmold and serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: favorite pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening just until evenly crumbly.
Add lemon juice, water and well beaten egg and mix lightly.
Roll out quickly and bake in a hot oven at 450°. Makes 2 double crust pies.
May be stored in waxed paper and in the refrigerator for a week or two.

title: bubble top chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
In medium bowl, combine chicken, broccoli, sour cream, water chestnuts, pimentos, onions, cheese and salt and pepper; blend well.
Spoon into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly around edges.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; cut each biscuit into fourths.
Remove chicken mixture from oven. Arrange biscuit pieces in single layer over hot chicken mixture. Bake for an additional 9 to 13 minutes or until biscuits are light golden brown.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sirloin tips in wine
directions: Brown meat in butter and oil in skillet. Add mushrooms. Stir in 3/4 cup bouillon, wine, soy sauce and onion salt; continue cooking. Remove meat from skillet into 2-quart casserole dish. Leave drippings.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine margarine and garlic. Set aside. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper and stir well. Dip each breast in butter mixture. Roll in crumb mixture. Roll tightly, starting at narrow end and secure with a wooden pick. Arrange rolls in a shallow baking pan. Drizzle with remaining margarine and lemon. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop cookie mix by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: vita crunch
directions: In a saucepan, mix the first 7 ingredients and bring to a boil.
In a large baking pan, mix all dry ingredients together and pour boiled mixture over all.
Mix well and bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and mix well.
Let cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: crunchies from microwave
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels on Medium power for 2 to 4 minutes. Mix ingredients together; spoon onto waxed paper to cool and harden.

title: bread buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
In large bowl, put sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir scalded milk in and let cool.
Add yeast and 1/2 of flour.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour slowly.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Work down.
Make into buns and let rise for 1 hour.
Makes about 20 buns.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jim's slider
directions: Clean, peel and cut up fruit.
Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, stir together soup and sour cream until smooth; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion and chili powder until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken, chilies and 2 tablespoon of soup mixture.
Remove from heat.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef cubes in frying pan with onion and mushrooms until lightly brown.
Pour into crock-pot with juices from frypan.
Add soups (undiluted) and mix together (sliced carrots and peppers are optional).
Simmer on low approximately 6 hours.
Pour over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dream cookie
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt in double boiler and bring to a hard boil.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Add undrained pineapple; cool until partially thickened.
Fold in topping, remaining marshmallows and mandarin oranges.
Chill until firm.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Blend
flour,
sugar and margarine; before adding other ingredients,
set
cup aside.	Then to remaining mixture, add baking
powder, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Then beat the 2 egg whites
and
fold
into mixture.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle
with
1 1/2 cups blueberries and rest of flour mixture on	top
of
blueberries.
Bake
at
350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: nana's cookies
directions: Mix well; chill dough in refrigerator before dropping by teaspoon. You can keep in the refrigerator for several days and bake as you wish. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty bean and barley soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water; bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until creamy.
Beat in sugar, then peanut butter. Add milk slowly, then fold in whipped topping until all ingredients are well mixed.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Can use a baked 8-inch crust, if desired.
Sprinkle nuts on top (optional).
Refrigerate several hours.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Make sauce of mushroom soup with enough water to mix.
Add cheese and let melt.
Melt butter and add crushed cracker crumbs.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix milk and egg yolks.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add the milk and egg mixture. Add pineapple and bread crumbs.
Beat egg whites separately and fold into mixture.
Bake 45 minutes in a baking dish sitting in another dish of water.
Bake at 375°.
Serves 10.

title: el paso bake
directions: Overlap the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan with tortillas. Beat eggs with milk, then add cheese and salsa.
Mix together.
Add meat, if desired.
Bake at 350° for good hour.
It's done when an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: squash-sour cream casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrot.
Fold into squash.
Combine stuffing and melted margarine.
Line bottom of 2-quart casserole with 1/2 of stuffing. Top with squash mixture.
Sprinkle generously with grated cheese. Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until bubbly and browned.

title: romaine toss
directions: Salad Dressing:
In container mix sugar, soy sauce and vinegar. Add olive oil, blending as it is needed.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and white sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream. Add salt, vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Prepare the nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon and mix together.
In Bundt (or loaf) pan, pour 1/3 batter.
Sprinkle 1/3 nut mixture and alternate layers, ending with nut mixture.
Then use a knife to cut through batter a few times.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't invert for 15 minutes after taking from oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pheasant
directions: Clean bird; cut for frying.
Combine flour, 2 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Place in paper bag with pieces of bird; shake. Melt butter in covered skillet; brown pheasant.
Pour sour cream mixed with remaining salt over meat.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: fig-strawberry jelly preserves
directions: Bring to a rolling boil for 5 minutes.
Pour into jelly jars and seal.
Yields 6 to 6 1/2 pints.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients together.
Mix other ingredients and add
dry ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or 1
hour for 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake in a large bowl with a spoon.
Do not use a mixer.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Heat milk and butter or margarine until the butter is melted.
Add to mixture. Add vanilla and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.
For sauce, stir together chicken broth, soy sauce, wine or water, cornstarch and red pepper.
Blend in peanut butter; set aside.
Preheat skillet; add oil.
Stir-fry garlic and ginger in hot oil for 15 seconds.
Add onion.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove vegetables. Add chicken.
Stir-fry until cooked.
Stir sauce.
Add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and stir to coat.
Heat through.
Serve on top of rice or linguine.
Serves 6.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut bread crossways, but not completely through.
Add fresh garlic to melted butter; put in bread slices with a spoon or pastry brush.
Pour remaining mixture across top.
Wrap in aluminum foil. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Simmer the first 6 ingredients together for 10 minutes.
Make a white sauce of flour, margarine, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until slightly thickened, then add to cooked vegetables (drain part of water but not all).
Add cheese and ham.
Cook just until cheese is melted, do not boil.
Serves 4 people.
You can adjust the amount of vegetables to your own liking.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Prepare according to package directions.
When pudding begins to thicken, add sour cream. Mix thoroughly; add vanilla and 1/2 of whipped topping.

title: beef zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini in salted water until tender.
Drain zucchini. In large skillet, brown onion and ground beef.
Pour off fat. Stir in bread crumbs, garlic powder, salt, pepper and oregano. Mixture will be dry.

title: cheese filled mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove
stems and place tops on cookie sheet.

title: moist coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package. Make cake in layer pans. Split layers and let cool. Mix together the sugar, sour cream and 1 package coconut. Put 1 cup of this mixture aside. Then pour the rest between layers, stacking the layers. Mix the 1 cup of mixture with 1 small bowl of Cool Whip. Put on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with the 2 packages of frozen coconut. Let set in refrigerator for 2 days before cutting. Store in refrigerator.

title: forgotten stew
directions: Put the stew meat, potatoes, carrots, onions and celery in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with tapioca. Combine tomato sauce and Coca-Cola and pour over the top. Cover tightly. Put in 250° oven and do not peek for 4 hours.

title: pignolatti
directions: Mix all of the ingredients
and knead for a few minutes to get a stiff dough.
Cut
dough
in
small pieces, roll into pencil size tube or rope and
cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch pieces. Deep fry in hot oil, about
350°, for about 4 1/2 to 5 minutes until medium brown.
Check
for
hardness.
If
overfried,
it will be tough.

title: summer sparkle punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in lemonade.
Add ginger ale and ice cubes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: barbecue sauce(one way to use little meatballs)
directions: Combine together the ingredients.
Place meatballs in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour on the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
Gradually add sugar mixture, mixing well.
Add chips.
Bake 12 minutes at 325 degrees on top rack.

title: almond sweets
directions: Soak the almonds in water for 12 hours, then drain and put them into boiling water.
Cover and leave for 10 minutes.
Drain almonds, remove skin and drop into cold water so that almonds do not discolor.
Grind the almonds with a little water in a coffee grinder.
Add sugar and cook in large pan on medium heat until the mixture forms into a dough.
Leave for 5 minutes.
Roll out the dough; mark into shapes and decorate with silver leaf.
Makes 15 pieces.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Phase:
12 hour soaking. Cooking Time:
15 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream room temperature cream cheese and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat after each one (electric mixer).
Add vanilla and beat.
Add sour cream and beat.
Pour into prepared spring-form pan (approximately 10 1/2 x 3-inch).
Bake 1 hour, then shut oven off.
Leave in oven for 2 hours without opening door.
Leave on counter for 2 hours, then put in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Cook beef in large skillet over medium-high heat until brown, stirring to separate meat; drain fat.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Add cream cheese, salt and chili powder; simmer 5 minutes.
Toss shells with butter; fill with beef mixture.
Arrange shells in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour taco sauce over each shell.
Cover with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 15 minutes.
Uncover, top with Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and chips.
Bake 15 minutes more or until bubbly.
Top with sour cream and chopped ripe olives.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 2 quart casserole, melt butter.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into casserole on top of melted butter.
Then pour peaches on top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it reaches 290°.
Add salt, butter and soda.
In a large greased bowl, pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Stir with buttered spoon to coat each kernel. Immediately form into balls and place on wax paper to cool.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Melt margarine on low heat in saucepan on stove.
Mix in brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Lay graham crackers singly in baking pan, then pour mixture over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Take out of oven and completely cool, then break into pieces.

title: three cheese puff
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in flour and baking powder. Stir in milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour all into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set or nicely browned.
May be made the night before and refrigerated.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container.
Mix well.
If not covered with liquid, add 1/2 cup or so of water.
Let set 2 hours; drain.
Do not rinse!

title: calzone
directions: Follow directions on bread package to rise.
Roll out dough into large circle.
On 1/2 of dough, spread on spaghetti sauce. Layer on top of sauce the meats and cheese and mushrooms.
Mix Ricotta cheese with eggs and parsley.
Lightly spread on other half of dough.
Fold cheese half over top of meat half.
Seal edges by pressing with fingers.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place a layer of each ingredient, starting with lettuce and ending with bacon.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours before serving.

title: make day before chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 package of stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Heat butter in water until melted and pour over stuffing. Mix chicken, onions, celery mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Beat eggs and add milk; pour over chicken mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, spread can of undiluted soup over chicken mixture. Top with remaining stuffing.
Drizzle 3/4 cube melted butter over top.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in small amount of fat.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook until soft, about 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Drain pineapple of all juice.
Add pineapple juice to batter instead of water.
If juice is not enough, add water to make 1/3 cup.
Bake as directed on package.
Mix vanilla pudding with milk; add cream cheese.
Beat well until all is blended, then fold in crushed pineapple.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of that, then top with coconut or nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey, onion and garlic in skillet.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp and split down the back to butterfly.
Add garlic salt
to flour.
Beat eggs and add to milk.
Dip shrimp in seasoned
flour, then the egg and milk, then in the saltine cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to directions on box (9 x 13 pan).
Remove from oven and poke holes in top with wooden spoon handle.
Pour cream of coconut over top.
Let sit until cake cools.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, 6 cups chicken broth, garlic and half of onions in a large pot; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until beans are tender, 2 to 3 hours.
Add additional broth if needed.

title: anna's green grape salad
directions: Melt butter on low; add flour and mix well.
Add milk and cook until thick (make white sauce).
Pour in marshmallows and stir until melted.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Will keep three days.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Peel and core apples, cut into 16 pieces.
Take one roll, place one slice of apple at large end and roll up.
Place into 9x13 baking dish.
When all rolls have been put into dish, melt butter, sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over rolls.
Pour Mountain Dew in between rolls.
Place in oven at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: chinese salad
directions: Break noodles into small bits. Add noodles to cabbage, almonds and sesame seeds and parsley.
Toss in chicken.
Just before serving, toss adding last three ingredients. Serves 6.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and sorghum.
Add egg and buttermilk and mix well.
Then add dry ingredients sifted together and vinegar-soda mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out thin with fingers dipped in flour.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked rigatoni casserole
directions: In large pot of water add salt and olive oil.
Cover when boiling.
Add rigatoni; cook 15 minutes.
Heat tomato sauce on low heat.
Cut cheese and margarine into slices.
Layer rigatoni, cheese and margarine in ovenproof dish or pan.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top is melted, around 15 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: brandied friendship fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart nonmetallic bowl, stirring gently.
Let stand, covered, at room temperature for 3 weeks, stirring twice a week.
Serve over ice cream or pound cake, reserving 1 cup of mixture for Starter.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 of the fruits to Starter every 1 to 3 weeks, alternating before serving.
Serve with ice cream or pound cake.
Yields 6 cups.

title: baked apple-noodle casserole
directions: Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon, salt and butter in a bowl. Toss together lightly, mash cream cheese and mix in sour cream. Add to previous mixture.
Add noodles, mixing lightly. Pour into a buttered casserole (2-quart).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: kraut salad
directions: Put kraut in colander and run cold water over it.
Drain. Heat vinegar and sugar until dissolved completely.
Cool slightly. Pour over mixture.
Let stand at least 3 hours.

title: oven meal
directions: 1. Place ingredients in 2 qt. casserole dish in the order given. Bake in oven at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take stems out of mushrooms.
Cut up mushroom stems and peppers. Melt butter in pan and saute stems and peppers.
Take off heat and mix cheese into the saute pan.
Mix in same pan 4 tablespoons of crackers and stuff the caps.
Sprinkle rest of crackers over top of the stuffed mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Pour off grease and drain well.
Cut crusts off bread; butter on one side and lay in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle sausage over bread and cheese over sausage.
In blender, combine eggs, milk, water and salt.
Blend together.
Pour over other ingredients; cover and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
When ready to bake, remove from refrigerator and let stand for 15 minutes while the oven preheats to 350°.
Then uncover and bake 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: polka-dotted hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: excellent pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all the ingredients, adding the water 1 tablespoon at a time.
Maybe a little more water will be needed. Roll out and make your crust.
Makes a double crust for a 9-inch pie.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add canned pineapple juice. Chill until slightly thickened. Mix crushed pineapple. Add cottage cheese and salt. Fold in jello. Chill until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple syrup.
Stir to dissolve.
Chill until partially set. Add remaining ingredients. Pour in mold.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Place pecans on a cookie sheet.
Melt margarine and coat pecans.
Place in the oven on broil until crisp.
Let cool.
Mix ice cream as usual and add pecans.
Fill to fill line in freezer with homogenized milk.

title: fudge
directions: Lay 2 sticks butter on top of powdered sugar and cocoa.
Add milk.
Place in microwave for 8 to 10 minutes; then beat until smooth by hand.
Pour into buttered pan and let it get cold.
Cut into squares.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Mix and let simmer, covered, for 20 minutes on low flame. While this mixture is simmering, cook 1 cup macaroni in 3 cups salted water.
Drain and add to first mixture.
Put in casserole; sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 500° for 15 minutes.

title: fast and easy chili
directions: Follow directions on Field chili log. Add cooked ground beef, beans and salsa. Cook until thoroughly heated. May need to add water or tomato juice for your desired consistency.

title: brownies
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: great for parties
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick, then grated cheese.
Work together and make long rolls.
Store in refrigerator 4 hours or freeze. Just before time to serve, cut in small pieces and bake at 325°. Good and easy.
Special for parties!

title: easy scallop jimmy
directions: In casserole, buttered, arrange the scallops.
Combine all ingredients but wine and lemon.
Sprinkle over scallops.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle on wine; garnish with a lemon twist and serve.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: creamy rhubarb pie
directions: Combine the egg, sour cream, sugar, salt and tapioca in a bowl.
Fill the pie shell with the rhubarb.
Pour the egg and cream mixture over rhubarb.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Lay in a shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Pour soup over balls and bake for 1/2 hour more.

title: lutz's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mash up egg yolks; mix with mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Add milk, salad dressing, salt and pepper to your taste.
Add onions, celery, green peppers and cut up egg whites.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra into about 1/4-inch slices.
Mix cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Roll okra in mixture.
Heat a heavy skillet with shortening in it.
Have it very hot when you add okra.
Leave on hot for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Keep stirring and turn to low; let fry slowly.
Every few minutes, stir to keep from sticking.
Will take about 25 minutes to cook.
Turn up heat last few minutes of cooking so will be crunchy.

title: spinach spaghetti lasagne pie
directions: Boil the spaghetti in salted water until tender. Drain.
Stir 2 tablespoons margarine into hot cooked spaghetti.
Stir in 2 beaten eggs and 1 cup Parmesan cheese.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a greased 10-inch pie plate.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add onion, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Add spices.
Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in order of listing in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pickled crab apples
directions: Wash and remove blossom ends and prick.
Bring vinegar, water, sugar, ginger, cinnamon and cloves (cinnamon and cloves tied in a bag) to a boil and add apples, a little at a time.
Remove before adding next batch.
Pour syrup over apples; let stand overnight. Remove bag of spices.
Pack apples in hot jars.
Bring syrup to a boil.
Pour over fruit.
Process 30 minutes.
Makes 16 to 20 pints.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar and add eggs, Ricotta and vanilla.
Sift together in a bowl the flour, baking powder and baking soda and mix well with other mixture.
Grease cookie sheet and drop teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: breakfast souffl
directions: Make the night before.

title: sweet and spicy mixed nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Butter a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; set aside.
In a medium bowl, lightly beat egg white with water.
Add nuts; stir until coated.
In another bowl, combine sugar, chili powder and red pepper; mix well.
Add nuts to sugar and spice mix.
Stir with a slotted spoon until well coated. Place in a single layer in prepared pan.
Bake until dry, 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool in pan.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: christmas coffee cake(may prepare ahead.  freezes well.  serves 8 to 10.)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix flour mixture alternately with sour cream; add vanilla.
Alternate cake mixture and filling in a greased tube pan beginning with batter and ending with filling on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in a gallon freezer. I put crushed pineapple in blender on high for a few minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Stir yeast, 1 cup water and sugar in small bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
In large bowl, put 2 cups water, honey, shortening and salt.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Beat in white flour.
Add whole wheat flour or enough to make moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Shape into ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size. Punch down.
Shape into loaves.
Put in pans.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil last 20 minutes if overbrowning.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in cake with large fork.
Pour (warmed) can of Eagle Brand milk over cake.
After cake has completely cooled, spread with Cool Whip and top with flaked coconut.

title: hamburger-corn bread casserole
directions: Brown and season 1 pound hamburger.
Add chopped onion and green peppers, 2 cups tomato sauce and any seasoning you like. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan with
grated
cheese on top.
Spread corn bread over cheese and meat.
Bake as for corn bread.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed. Add Cool Whip and condensed milk. Cover bottom of large pan with mix. Add a layer of vanilla wafers. Cover with mix. Add layer of sliced bananas. Cover with mix. Repeat until all ingredients are used. End with a layer of mix. Chill and serve.

title: ham & red-eye gravy
directions: Prepare grits per directions on pkg. While grits are cooking, heat a cast iron skillet. Add ham to skillet. Brown on both sides about 5 minutes. Remove ham to large plate. Stir coffee in cup of boiling water, then in skillet. Stir constantly for 1 minute. Grandma keeps ham and grits separated on serving plate, and pours gravy over entire plate.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Cream the cream cheese and ham together.
Beat until creamy; add parsley and onion.
Add Tabasco sauce last.
Refrigerate.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: In a skillet or wok, fry bacon until crisp and remove.
To the bacon drippings, add onion, cabbage, cayenne, ginger and soy.
Cook over medium heat until the cabbage and onions are very soft and wilted.
Add the crumbled bacon and stir.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry crunch coffeecake
directions: Position a rack in the lower third of the oven.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease and 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch (6 cup) loaf pan. Combine almonds and brown sugar and sprinkle in the bottom of the pan.
Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together thoroughly in a large bowl.
Add butter and cut butter with 2 knives or a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Do not allow the butter to melt or form a blended paste with the flour.
Whisk together in another bowl, egg, milk and vanilla and pour over the flour mixture.
Stir until about three quarters of the dry ingredients are moistened.
Add blueberries. Fold just until the dry ingredients are moistened and the berries are distributed.
Spoon the batter into the pan and spread evenly. Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. (Other than the juice from the berries).
Bake 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in the pan on a rack for 5 to 10 minutes.
Loosen the edges if necessary and invert onto the rack.
Serve warm.

title: sour cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add cherries.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes; 350° for 25 minutes.
Good in a bowl of milk.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together.
Don't overbeat.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip cream cheese and juice from the cherries.
In separate bowl, whip the whipping cream until stiff.
Combine cherries and 1/2 to 3/4 bag of marshmallows into whipped cream.
Drain pineapple and add cream cheese.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and orange concentrate.
Allow to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use either dish or mold. Mold may be greased slightly.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients, except noodles, and bring to a boil.
Put half of the meat mixture in a casserole dish; add all of the uncooked noodles.
Put rest of meat mixture on top. Cook covered in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cup
directions: Mix fruit juices, Tang and pudding. Spread over fruit dish. Place strawberries on top.

title: a different sandwich
directions: Take one slice of bread.
Place on table.
Cut tomato into 4 slices.
Place 2 on slice of bread.
Cut bell pepper into 4 slices. Place 2 on slice of bread.
Place large piece (big enough to cover sandwich) of Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Place in microwave for 45 seconds or until cheese melts.
Repeat 3 more times.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, shell and devein shrimp; rinse with running cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in 2 tablespoons hot butter or margarine (1/4 stick), cook shrimp, stirring frequently, until shrimp turn pink and are tender, about 5 minutes.
With slotted spoon remove shrimp to bowl.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, on wax paper.
Pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat mixture. Starting from short end, roll up meat, using wax paper to lift. Seal all edges well.
Place roll seam side down in a baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all except cheese into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: low-fat nachos
directions: Preheat broiler.
Arrange tortilla chips on a nonstick baking pan.
In a small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Spoon over chips.
Broil nachos until brown and bubbling, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach enough to thaw; drain and squeeze out all liquid. Combine all 4 ingredients.
Serve with veggies or crackers.
This dip is so good it is usually even enjoyed by people who dislike spinach.

title: overnight cucumbers
directions: Slice the cucumbers and onion into a container with a cover. Mix sour cream with sugar to taste.
Pour over cucumbers and onion, folding into the vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: knockwurst and sauerkraut
directions: In large frying pan, add oil.
Saute onions until translucent. Add the catsup, water, brown sugar and mustard.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: pasta broccoli
directions: Heat oil in skillet on high.
Add onion and broccoli and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add regular water; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in tomatoes, garlic and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes longer or until broccoli is tender.
Put pasta in bowl.
Add broccoli, cheese and reserved water.
Stir until blended and creamy.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix all together and press into bottom and sides of pie plate.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix by hand until smooth.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan or large Bundt pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking dish.
Top each pork chop with a slice of onion and a ring of pepper.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chops.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel peanut balls
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine nuts, sweetened condensed milk and vanilla. Over medium heat, cook and stir 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture forms ball around spoon and pulls away from side of pan. Cool 10 minutes. Chill if desired.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In small heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt confectioners coating. With wooden pick, dip each ball into melted coating, covering half of ball. Place on wax paper-lined baking sheets until firm.
Store covered at room temperature or in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken breasts with asparagus(a colorful and delicious dish)
directions: In a skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove and set aside.
Spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk and pepper.
Stir in asparagus.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and asparagus is tender-crisp, stirring often.
Serves 4.

title: raisin squares
directions: Cook 1 cup raisins in 1 cup water.
Mix sugar and flour then butter.
Mix 1/2 cup raisin water with 1/2 teaspoon soda and add to this mixture.
Add egg, vanilla and 1 cup raisins.
Mix all ingredients well, then spread on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and pineapple together.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Ready to eat in about 30 minutes.

title: alice's chicken and broccoli
directions: Poach chicken; skin and debone.
Cut into long slices.	Line a baking dish with cooked broccoli.
Stir soups, mayonnaise and curry powder together.
Pour half over broccoli.	Put chicken slices on top and cover with balance of soup mixture.
Cover with cheese. Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cheese cake
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs and blend with oleo and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Press into glass 9 x 13-inch or larger pan. Warm in oven for 5 minutes.

title: pork and beans sandwich
directions: Spread pork and beans over top of bread slice.
Top with slice of cheese.
Sprinkle with diced onion.
Place 2 slices of bacon on top and place under broiler until bacon is done. Great with glass of milk.
This could be done in a microwave if the bacon was precooked.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in the fat; add the green pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients together and stir well.
Then add these ingredients to the meat.
Cover with a lid and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: pot pie
directions: Use any meat that you have.
This is just as good with leftover beef as it is with turkey.

title: cocoa peanut butter mounds
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to the boiling point, stirring constantly, and boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in rolled oats.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool thoroughly before serving or storing.

title: turkey chow mein
directions: Heat margarine in a large frying pan.
Saute green pepper and celery for 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Blend cornstarch with cold water and soy sauce.
Gradually stir into broth.
Add onion soup mix.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add turkey, mushrooms, water chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Pour over ribs or chicken.

title: divinity
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar, water and salt to a boil, boil 3 minutes.
Pour all at once into marshmallow cream and beat until mixture begins to thicken and stiffen.
Add vanilla and nuts quickly and spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: hawaiian delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, cream cheese and marshmallows in 2 cups hot water.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill until thick.
Stir in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: bean soup
directions: Cover ham bone with water in large pot.
Add beans and onions and cook a total of 6 1/2 hours over medium heat.
Add water as needed.
After 4 hours, add tomatoes.
After 5 hours, remove bone. Let cool and pick off remaining ham.
Add ham to soup, along with savory.
Freezes well.

title: baked eggs
directions: Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over bread.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Place pan in another pan with water.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
May put cooked bacon or sausage on top when done.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserve 1/3 cup liquid.
Place beets in a large 1-quart casserole with sugar, beet liquid and vinegar.
Tie spice in a small square of cheesecloth and add to beets.
Cook, covered for 6 to 7 minutes or until mixture boils.
Cool and remove bag of spices.
Refrigerate up to 2 weeks.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place meat in baking dish.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Heat for 15 minutes.
Serve in mini crock.

title: festive fish fillets
directions: Thaw fish.
Remove skin and cut into serving pieces.
Dip fish in dressing and roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on nonstick or well-greased cookie sheet.
Drizzle butter over fish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 500°
for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel and slice peaches; place in bowl and add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Set aside for 1/2 hour.
In a shallow dish, melt butter. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk and stir.
Pour batter into baking dish over butter.
Spread evenly.
Top batter with peaches including juice.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Batter rises to top.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the sugar and eggs.
Add melted margarine, orange juice and salt.
Add noodles, raisins and apple filling and mix well.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with corn flake crumbs.

title: broccoli cauliflower bake
directions: Thaw vegetables and drain well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with drained mushrooms.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese is melted and mixture is hot and creamy.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with onion rings and cover and bake for 30 minutes more.
Terrific dish!

title: baked beans
directions: Place in crock - pot and cook until bacon is done.
1/2 day.

title: cherry pecan cake
directions: Combine cherries, pecans and 1/4 cup flour; set aside.
Cream oleo, 2 cups sugar and mace until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add remaining flour alternately with orange juice to creamed mixture. Add cherries and mix.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add remaining sugar and beat until stiff, glossy peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.

title: lemon-blueberry muffins
directions: Line 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Toss berries with 3 tablespoons of flour mixture in small bowl. Coat well.

title: chickeny cheesy noodles
directions: In a 4 to 6-quart pot, fix noodles as per instructions on package.
Drain cooked noodles thoroughly and add chicken broth and cubed cheese.
Add 3 or 4 good shakes of the seasoned salt and stir the mixture to cover the cheese.
Don't sit the pot back on the hot burner as it will stick the noodles to the bottom of the pot.
Let set for about 5 to 7 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Stir slightly to assure that the noodles are covered with cheese.
Makes about 8 cups and will serve 8.

title: dot taylor's party punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar and water.
Chill several hours.
Pour mixture over ice ring in a punch bowl; add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly.

title: sausage-vegetable dinner
directions: Cut sausage diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Wash potatoes; cut into 1/3-inch crosswise sections.
Layer sausage, potatoes and next 5 ingredients in order given in a large Dutch oven, sprinkling each vegetable layer with salt and pepper.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 35 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef bundles
directions: Mix milk and beef.
Divide the mixture into 4 or 5 portions and flatten into patties.
Make 1 cup of stuffing.
Place equal amounts of stuffing on each patty.
Fold patty in half and seal edges. Place in baking dish.
Heat can of undiluted soup until bubbly. Add Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Pour over patties.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain grease and add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: lime chutney
directions: In stainless steel or enamel kettle, combine lime juice, peel, vinegar, sugar, ginger root, onion and raisins.
Grind together the coriander seed, mustard seed, peppercorns and cloves.
Add mixture to kettle with cinnamon, cardamom, cayenne and salt.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 40 to 50 minutes until sauce thickens.
Ladle the chutney into sterilized jars.
Makes 1 quart.
Best if stored in 1/2-pint jars.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Form ball and serve with Triscuits or crackers of choice.

title: hi-d's monkey on a stick
directions: Cut pork into small cubes.
Combine the Sprite, shoyu and onions to make a marinade.
Marinate the pork overnight.
Skewer meat and BBQ.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in tomatoes and 1 can of water until tender. Brown meat with chopped onions.
Using a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer the macaroni mix, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat this process.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
This may be frozen or refrigerated until ready to use.
If mixture is cold, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water before baking.

title: green jello salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cream cheese (cut in chunks).
Whip with mixer.
Cool in refrigerator. Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well with mixer and stir in pecans.
Refrigerate in cut glass bowl or salad mold.

title: layered tossed salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, celery, peppers, water chestnuts, onions and peas.
Spread with a generous layer of Miracle Whip, adding 1 teaspoon sugar.
Top with a good layer of Romano cheese.
One may also add fresh mushrooms, sliced cucumbers, crumbled bacon, sliced eggs and/or cherry tomatoes, if so desired.
Cover with foil and make a day ahead of time.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine dry cake mix with melted butter.
Take out 1 1/2 cups; set aside for topping.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Drain water from corn and beans.
In a bowl, combine and mix beans, corn, sour cream and celery soup.
Saute onion in small amount of butter until tender.
Add sauteed onion to mix.
Mix well and place in a well-greased baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Crush Ritz crackers and coat with melted butter.
Sprinkle crackers on top of cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in oven at 350° or until bubbly and brown.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine breads and enough broth to make mixture consistency of uncooked corn batter.
Skim fat from broth adding to bread.
Add celery, onion, butter and eggs.
Bake in medium oven until done or brown.
If you are going to make gravy, save a big cooking spoon of the dressing, uncooked, and stir it in with your gravy.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add diced tomatoes and diced peppers. Add remaining ingredients and mix all together.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat all ingredients, except shrimp, to blend, then pour evenly over shrimp in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 6 hours.
Broil in marinade (turning once) until brown. Serve over linguine.
Serves 4.

title: mcelhaney's tex-mex trail chili
directions: Brown onion, garlic and meat in small amount of oil.
Add salt, cumin and chili powder.
Stir.
Add water, bouillon cube and beans.
Simmer at least 1/2 hour.
This chili is better if make ahead and reheated.

title: momma hardester's nut cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Then work in the softened shortening until the consistency of corn meal.
Add the eggs and 1/2 the milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add the remainder of milk and the flavoring.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Fold in the chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured tube pan.

title: peach jello
directions: Dissolve 1 package of peach Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and 2 cups vanilla ice cream.
Put in mold and set 1 hour.
Dissolve 1 package peach Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Cool, but do not put in refrigerator.
Put peach slices on top of molded Jell-O and pour plain Jell-O over the top.
Chill.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix together and pour in a cooked pie shell.
Serve cold.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion in skillet and season with salt and pepper.
Add soup, enchilada sauce and milk.
Line oblong pan with 1/2 tortilla shells and top with meat mixture and 1/2 cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with sour cream to serve.

title: twenty-four hour lettuce salad
directions: Break
lettuce	into
bite-size
pieces
and
spread on bottom of dish.
Sprinkle peas over lettuce.
Sprinkle onions, celery, chestnuts, sugar, eggs and tomatoes over peas.
Place mayonnaise on	top to seal.
Sprinkle with cheese and garnish with bacon.

title: diabetic spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add meat and brown.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour uncovered.
Serving size is 1/2 cup. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wash potatoes.
Scrub well.
Dry on paper towel.
Prick potato skins with fork.
Rub each potato well with about 1 teaspoon of shortening.
Wrap each potato in aluminum foil.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Unwrap.
Split potato, not all the way through.
Fill split with margarine.

title: shrimp fra diavolo
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in saucepan for 3 minutes.
Add pepper flakes; saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp that has been peeled, deveined and halved lengthwise; simmer until shrimp are translucent, 5 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Top with sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 3 small (or 2 large) loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 325°. Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Sift flour with soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture and mix in zucchini and raisins, nuts or dates.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.

title: giant sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add eggs, oil, salt and vanilla. Mix well.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Finely chop mushroom stems; saute with onions in butter for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add a little at a time: cake flour and chopped pecans.
Roll into small balls and bake on greased cookie sheet at 300°
for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
These freeze well.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine together.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together (whip until creamy).
Mix Dream Whip and milk together (cream and beat until stiff). Then add creamed cheese and sugar mixture, mix well.
Spread 1/2 crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Spread 1/2 Dream Whip mixture on crumbs.
Spread cherry pie filling next.
Spread balance of Dream Whip on top of cherries.
Spread balance of cracker crumbs on top.
Let set 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Let cranberries set in 1 3/4 cup sugar for 1 hour.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 cups of hot water.
Dice celery.
Chop nuts.
Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.

Add oil and stir until thoroughly mixed, then add vinegar and lemon juice, a few drops at a time and beat until an emulsion is formed or ingredients may be placed in a bottle and shaken vigorously together to form an emulsion.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Pour off grease. Add taco sauce, chillies, tomato sauce, taco seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, A.1. sauce, bell pepper and onion.
Simmer for 1 hour or more.
Heat taco shells; put in meat.
Add cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Sift first three ingredients together.	Boil oil, water and cocoa and pour over flour mixture.	Add eggs, buttermilk with soda dissolved in it and add vanilla.
Pour in brownie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Using a wire whisk, mix dry ingredients thoroughly. Set aside.
In a large bowl, using electric mixer, combine sugars on medium speed until blended to a uniform color.
Add butter.
Mix at low speed to break into 1-inch chunks.
Increase mixer speed and completely cream the butter into the sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix until blended.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix on low speed until dough has formed with a light dusting of unblended flour.
Add Mrs. Field's chocolate chips and walnuts.
Mix on low speed until blended.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet, spacing them 2-inches apart.
Bake for 22 to 24 minutes at 300°.
Transfer from hot baking sheet to cool surface immediately. Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sonara salsa
directions: Fire roast the chile by placing it directly in the flame of gas burner or laying it on a electric burner.
Rotate slowly until skin is darkened and blistered.
Place on cutting board and scrape skin off.
Skin should slide off easily.
If not, place back in fire.
Remove seeds and chop coarsely.
Place tomatoes, chilies, onions and seasonings in blender for 30 seconds.
Add cilantro and pulse for 5 seconds.
Place in the fridge for 30 minutes to chill. Enjoy!

title: pebbles cupcakes
directions: Microwave butter in 4 quart microwavable bowl on high for 45 seconds, or until melted.
Add marshmallows; mix to coat. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes or until marshmallows are melted and smooth, stirring after 45 seconds.
Add cereal; mix to coat well.

title: date torte cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating until thick.
Sift together dry ingredients; mix in the dates and walnuts.
Fold into egg mixture.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Cut in 16 squares.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: paul's pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange chops in baking dish.
Top with onion slices.
Add spices and soy sauce.
Add enough water to just cover everything.
Cover dish with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: peppers stuffed with tuna
directions: Mix together tuna, bread crumbs and tomato pulp.
Add salt, pepper and onion juice.
Cut slice from stem end of peppers and remove seeds.
Then parboil peppers for 3 minutes.
Cool them. Place in muffin tins and fill with tuna mixture.
Cover with buttered crumbs, top with cheese and bake 20 minutes.
Cover with your favorite sauce.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise and soup.
Mix well.
Add onion.
Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in greased dish.
Top with 1 cup Cheddar cheese and 1 cup Ritz cracker crumbs.
Pour 1/3 cup melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbles.

title: toasty cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast bread; butter both sides.
Cook and stir meat, onion, celery, prepared mustard and salt until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Alternate layers of toast, meat mixture and cheese in greased baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over layers in pan.
If you wish, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Spread chicken breasts open.
Arrange in large baking pan. Sprinkle with seasoning and onion.
In a bowl, blend flour and orange juice until smooth.
Pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, 1 hour in a 300° oven.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour and brown in oil.
Place in casserole with mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Stir garlic and spices with tomatoes; pour over chicken.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4
inch thick.
Cut into 1/4 inch wide strips.
Sprinkle meat with paprika and allow to stand.
Brown meat in butter; add
garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
(Or for
really
tender
meat
simmer for about 1 hour. Remember to check
to
be sure liquid does not all cook away.)

title: claire's yummy instant cupcakes
directions: Slightly soften ice cream.
Stir until it is the same consistency as frosting.
Frost the muffin with the ice cream. Decorate the cupcake.
Eat.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, garlic salt and pepper in a 3-quart Dutch oven.
Cook until beef loses redness. Add flour and stir well.
Add undrained mushrooms and soup.
Stir well and bring to a bubbling heat.
Add sour cream and chow mein noodles.
Stir well and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma elizabeth's date nut bread
directions: Chop dates and add boiling water, soda and butter.
Let stand until cool.
Beat egg; add sugar.
Add cooled mixture, flour, nuts, salt and vanilla.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Stir butter, eggs and Parmesan cheese into noodles. Form mixture into 10-inch pie pan. In skillet, cook beef and onion. Drain off fat. Stir in jar of spaghetti sauce. Pour on top of noodles. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix soft.
Roll, cut and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cucumber party slices
directions: Mix dressing mix with cream cheese and spread on rye bread slices.
Cut cucumbers thin to medium and place on each slice of bread.
Serve chilled.

title: sugared salmon
directions: Preheat the broiler. Spray the broiler pan with nonstick spray. Whisk together the brown sugar, mustard and dill in a small bowl. Place salmon on broiler rack and cook 4 minutes (about 7-inches from the broiler heat). Take out and spoon the sugar mixture on the salmon. Broil 5 minutes more.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt butter and add pretzels and sugar.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzel layer. Dissolve jello; add strawberries.
Stir and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Put in refrigerator to let thicken.

title: jim's salsa sauce
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and simmer until thick, about 1 hour.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Beat margarine and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and walnuts.
Take enough dough and cover each candy kiss.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes (not brown, just set).
Do not remove from cookie sheet until cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container.
Do not refrigerate or freeze.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: In bowl, combine cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise. Let stand 30 minutes.
Spread on rye bread; top with cucumbers. Slice and garnish with dill.

title: butternut spread(traditional)
directions: Gather a quantity of butternuts.
Crack nuts and separate meats from shells.
Grind nuts to paste.
Traditionally, this was done on the grinding stone in much the way as corn was ground. Spread is eaten with bread or corn cakes.

title: honey candy
directions: Combine honey,	peanut	butter,
dried	milk
and wheat germ. Shape into small balls.
Roll each ball in crushed corn flakes and enjoy.

title: wellesly coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating with each addition.
Add sour cream, vanilla and almonds; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to mixture and beat.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, pecans and cinnamon for filling.
Place 1/3 batter in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 filling mixture.
Spoon in rest of batter and sprinkle with remaining filling.
Bake 1 hour.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour.
Let rise until double in amount.
Shape into rolls.
Place into greased pans.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: corned beef roll
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Add corned beef.
Roll into a ball and garnish with parsley.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and let cool.

title: magic bars
directions: Put ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed in a layer-like manner.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Take chicken off bone; cut up.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple jewel squares
directions: Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and the butter.
Press into bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish; chill.
Thoroughly drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple syrup; cool.
Blend cream cheese with 3 tablespoons sugar, the vanilla and orange peel. Stir 1/2 cup gelatin into drained pineapple; set aside.
Gradually blend remaining gelatin into cream cheese mixture.
Stir in sour cream. Pour into crust; chill.
Chill until firm.
Spoon pineapple mixture evenly over cream cheese layer.
Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Yields 6 to 9 servings.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in mixer or blender; chill before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks or longer.
This is very similar to John's Restaurant.

title: zi sofi's cookies
directions: Roll out dough to approximately 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out with cookie cutter the size of liquor glass.
Do not grease pan heavily.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until nicely brown.

title: fancy flounder roll-ups
directions: Divide broccoli spears on top of fillets; roll up and secure with toothpicks. Arrange in 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, spices and part of the water.
Pour over the apples.
Pour water over rest of the ingredients.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Put in jars and seal.
No need to cold pack.
Jars seal themselves.

title: freezer bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed; pour over cucumber mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 day.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Mix tomato juice with soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Corn Flakes and butter and put into greased casserole dish. Top with 2 cups crushed Corn Flakes mixed with 1/2 cup melted butter. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Makes a lot.

title: mack's cucumber and onion pickles
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, minced garlic and salt; cool.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and onions.
This will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour cookie or jelly roll pan.
Mix together sifted flour, salt, sour cream, sugar, baking powder and eggs. Bring to a boil 2 sticks butter, 1 cup water and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mock margarita punch
directions: In 4-quart non-metal container, combine lemonade and limeade concentrates, egg whites, powdered sugar and crushed ice; mix well.
Cover; freeze, stirring occasionally. Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Spoon 2 cups slush mixture into blender; add 1 cup club soda.
Cover; blend until frothy.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a 7 or 8-inch flowerpot for this recipe.
If you use a clay pot, be sure and bake the pot for 20 minutes at 350°. Do not wash; clay will absorb water.
It is best to use a plastic flowerpot.

title: curry chicken on rice
directions: Saute chicken in butter.
Add 2 cups chicken bouillon.
Add apples and onions.
Add curry powder.
Simmer about 1 hour or until good consistency to serve over rice.
Serve over white rice. Salted peanuts or chutney are nice, served on the side.

title: spinach-artichoke bake
directions: Arrange artichokes in shallow 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Mix spinach and cream cheese; season with desired amount of butter, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour over artichokes.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese things
directions: Mix together with hands.
(Most of the time I let sit in refrigerator overnight or until ready to fix; makes it easier to roll.)
Roll into balls and put on a cookie sheet.
Press whole pecan into center of each ball.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook bouillon cubes, water, celery and onions for 20 minutes, covered.
Add potatoes, carrots and frozen mixed vegetables. Cook 30 minutes, covered.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir.
Easy and delicious!!!

title: peachy rhubarb pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup; chop the peaches.
Place peaches and syrup in a bowl;
add rhubarb, sugar, coconut, tapioca and vanilla.
Line a 9 inch pie plate with the bottom pastry.
Add filling;
dot with butter.
