Top with remaining pastry or a lattice crust;
flute edges.
If using a full top crust, cut slits in it. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and pecans in greased cake pan (9 x 13-inch). Mix cake mix following directions on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Cream margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls all over unbaked cake in pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: one-dish choco-nut bars
directions: Place butter/margarine in 8 x 8-inch square microwave-safe dish and microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted. Stir in sugars and water to blend well.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour and baking powder in sifter; sift into creamed mixture with salt, stirring to blend well.
Fold in coconut, chocolate pieces and half the nuts.
Spread remaining nuts evenly over top of batter, pressing in lightly.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients except muffin mix.
Stir well and then add mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until center is done.
You may also bake in two loaf pans.

title: grandma's vegetable soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except rice and macaroni for 45 minutes.
Add rice and macaroni; cook for 20 minutes longer.
May be seasoned with beef or beef stock, also.

title: sauteed cauliflower
directions: Quickly cook cauliflower in boiling, salted water, 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain well and slice very thin or chop coarse.
Texture will be crisp and center may be be warmed through, but no matter. Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add cauliflower and toss well over very, very, low heat until most of butter has been absorbed. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Squeeze lemon juice over it.
Very tasty.

title: ship wreck
directions: Slice potatoes into a buttered casserole dish.
Crumble hamburger over them.
Add salt and pepper.
Put onion over hamburger, then the beans.
Cover all with tomato soup.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and delicious dessert
directions: Spread can of pie filling in baking dish.
Over this sprinkle the cake mix. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle the coconut and pecans over this. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Take leftover sugar and put in cup and add brown sugar to make 1 cup.
Cook with 1/2 cup of margarine until smooth.
Pour over biscuits and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: two-toned walnut jumbles
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs; continue beating until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup of the walnuts.
Sift flour together with soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Divide dough into halves, in separate bowls.
Stir melted chocolate into one of the bowls of dough.

title: muffin heads(kid's snack)
directions: Toast English muffin halves as usual.
Cover muffins with peanut butter and/or jelly.
Using some of the listed ingredients and your imagination, make a funny face.
Eat 'em up!!!!!

title: spinach salad
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain and squeeze as much liquid as possible from the spinach.
Add mayonnaise and chopped onion.
Mix well and press into a salad ring or small bowl.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Place ring or salad bowl upside-down on a plate and shake gently to unmold.
Place peppers around outside.
Enjoy! Also good as a dip.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup Ritz crackers,
tablespoons butter and dehydrated onion in large bowl and
mix
together thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour in a 1-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small
bowl
and
sprinkle
evenly
over top. Bake until golden, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except flour tortillas.
Spread this mixture on each flour tortilla; roll up tightly and place in airtight container.
Or, you can wrap each roll up in foil or plastic wrap.
Put in refrigerator at least 3 hours before serving.
(They are better if refrigerated overnight.)

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine and toss with crushed crackers.
Spread on top of casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date snowballs
directions: Heat in saucepan 1 stick margarine until melted.
Remove from heat and add finely cut dates, sugar and beaten egg.
Mix well. Return to heat and cook mixture for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Lower heat so mixture just simmers.
Cool 20 minutes, then add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Refrigerate for 1 hour, then roll into small balls.
Roll each ball in coconut.
Store in refrigerator in tight container.

title: sirloin tips over rice or noodles
directions: Brown meat in oil in Dutch oven or stew pot. Add beef broth, wine and soy sauce.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour or until meat is tender. Add mushrooms, green pepper and garlic powder.
Let simmer for another 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water. Add to sirloin mixture. Stir until thickened. Serve over warm rice or egg noodles.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until a knife comes out of the custard clean.

title: chicken ramen salad
directions: Brown almonds, sesame seed and sunflower seeds in 2 tablespoons oil.
Chop cabbage, green onion and bell pepper fine. Mix all together.
Add Top Ramen (uncooked), broken into small pieces.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut all fruit into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Should be eaten within 24 hours.

title: chocolate ice cream pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and let cool.
Line pan with vanilla wafers and alternate ice cream and cooled chocolate sauce. Sprinkle top with nuts and keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in percolator for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Bring all ingredients, except eggs, to a hard boil.
Pour over hard-boiled eggs.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 or more days.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and milk.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 236° to 238°; cool to 220°. Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls on marble or wax paper.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and reserve juice.
Mix fruit in a large bowl. Measure juice from fruit and add enough orange juice to make 2 cups.
Add pie filling to juice and mix well, then pour over fruit and mix well again.
Chill well.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, water and rice together in large casserole baking dish. Salt chicken and place in dish.
Cook approximately 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Saute sausage and onion.
Drain well.
Melt cheese.
Mix together all ingredients.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator. Serve at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: broiled steak a la charlton heston
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a blender.
Spread mixture on both sides of steak.
Place coated steak in a plastic bag and seal.
Marinate overnight.
Broil or barbecue to rare or medium-rare.
Do not cook until well done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Range Top:
Cook and stir onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in hot oil over medium-high heat until tender, but not browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in beans with liquid and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Blend eggs, one at a time.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake. We leave out the raisins and put lots of pecans.

title: shrimp and gravy
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and shrimp.
Saute until shrimp are pink or orange.
Add gravy mix, seasonings and water. Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: spaghetti with green pepper and tomato sauce
directions: Mix tomatoes, peppers, onions, garlic, oil, salt and pepper in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are very tender. Cook pasta as directed on package; drain. Toss pasta and cheese with hot vegetable sauce. Makes 12 servings.

title: peanut butter bars(microwave)
directions: Place butter and peanut butter in 1-quart glass bowl. Microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir; add cracker crumbs and sugar and mix well.
Press in 8-inch square pan.
Place chips and oil in 1-cup glass container.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Mix and spread on top of crumb mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Then cut in 1-inch squares.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. Cut in oleo until crumbly. Press onto bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: double cheese meat roll
directions: Combine hamburger, eggs, crackers, onion, 1/2 c tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix well and shape into flat rectangle about 10 x 12 on wax paper.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese evenly over meat.
Roll like a jelly roll and press ends to seal.
Bake in a shallow baking dish at 350 F for 1 hr.
Drain excess fat, pour remaining tomato sauce and sprinkle cheese over and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tomato halves cut side up in baking dish.
Mix all remaining ingredients and mound an equal amount on each tomato half.
Bake about 20 minutes or until golden on top.

title: chocolate chip mint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix beaten egg, vanilla and mint extracts.
In separate bowl, combine flour, wheat germ and baking powder.
Stir into the butter and sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoons of batter onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: g-man hellsfire chili
directions: Cook beans per package.
When half done, pour off the water and cook the rest of the way with beef broth, covered about 1-inch with (topped off) water (large pot).

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix together margarine and graham crackers.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Put in dish from bottom to top in the following order:
graham cracker mix, cream cheese filling, cherry pie filling, graham cracker mix.
Chill.

title: milky way cake
directions: Heat Milky Way bars, margarine and pecans until melted. Cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix soda with buttermilk, add to sugar mixture.
Fold in candy mixture.

title: christmas odor punch
directions: Place all ingredients in large cooking kettle; allow to come to a boil for several minutes, then turn heat down to simmer, allowing the room to fill with a wonderful Christmas odor.
Add water and stir as needed.

title: rosy punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Cool.
Stir in cranberry, lime and orange juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale at serving time. Garnish with lime slices.
Makes 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: bisquick rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Roll into 12 ball shapes. Spread 1/4 cup mix on plate.
Roll each ball in mix and put into greased muffin pan.
Bake 15-20 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp and fried rice
directions: Put 3 tablespoons cooking oil in frying pan.
Chop and brown the pepper and onion.
Put in a casserole.
Add 3 more tablespoons cooking oil.
Put in the uncooked rice and fry until golden, stirring occasionally.
While that is cooking, put consomme and shrimp into casserole.
Pour in rice and stir the whole mixture. Bake in oven at moderate temperature for an hour.
Serve with a good green salad and any kind of dessert.
Good!

title: seafood casserole
directions: Boil water, add seafood and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove seafood; set aside.

title: ground beef t-bones
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well and chill. Shape mixture in 4 T-bone shaped patties. Broil 6 minutes on each side.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with pinch of sugar.
In a large mixing bowl combine potato flakes, sugar, shortening, salt and scalded milk.
When cool, add yeast, egg and flour.
Beat flour in until heavy on beaters. Lift beaters and add flour with fork until stiff.
Knead dough.
Divide into 2 parts.
Store in plastic bags (spray bags with butter Pam).
Remove from refrigerator and make rolls.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown beef or deer in skillet.
Drain meat.
Mix meat and all other ingredients.
Cook on low heat in crock-pot for 4 hours. This makes a thick, rich, milk chili.
Add water during cooking if a thinner chili is desired.

title: beans and escarole
directions: Wash the escarole and cut it into 1-inch strips.
In a large pot, heat the oil and garlic for 2 minutes.
Discard the garlic, add the tomatoes and salt, cover and cook 5 minutes.
Take the escarole out of the water and put it in the pan with the water that clings to the leaves.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes, stirring now and then.
Add the beans and black pepper and cook 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Note:
The cut size of chicken is like the one we buy at "Kentucky Fried" except for the breast.
Cut in half more.

title: shrimp 'n aspic
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add gelatin which has been softened in cold water.
Add lemon juice, pimento, celery and horseradish.
Pour into ring mold.
Chil until firm. Unmold and fill with chilled, cleaned shrimp.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Brown the beef until done in oil.
Add onions, green peppers, tomatoes, steak sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and parsley. Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni with salt and drain.
Add beef to mixture.
Gently spoon mushroom soup over the top of the mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In large bowl combine 1 cup flour and yeast.
In saucepan heat water, sugar and salt until warm, stirring to dissolve.
Add to dry mixture in bowl.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes on high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Shape into ball.
Place in lightly greased bowl; turn (to grease other side).
Cover; let rise until double (1 hour).
Punch down and cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Grease 1 quart casserole; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Place dough in casserole; sprinkle top with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise until double (30 to 45 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil if top browns too quickly.
Remove from dish; cool.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put rice in small casserole dish (1 1/2-quart size).
Pour soups over rice.
Do not add any water.
Cut margarine into small pieces and put on top.
Put lid on dish and cook for 55 minutes at 350°.
Stir after taking out of oven.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Slice 6 potatoes, layer chopped onion, layer cream style corn. Repeat recipe in layers.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on each layer. Add 1 can tomatoes on top.
Brown sausage.
Place on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour then turn down to 350°.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together in large bowl, stir in eggs and then butter. Put in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until nicely browned.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
In punch bowl, crumble 1/3 of cake, then layer 1/2 of the vanilla pudding. Spread to edge of bowl.
Add 1 can of the cherry pie filling, followed by 1 can of the drained pineapple.
Then layer next sliced bananas.
Then 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Top with pecans.

title: "some more's"
directions: Toast a marshmallow over a campfire until it is golden brown. Slip it between two graham crackers which are lined with two sections from a Hershey bar.
The hot marshmallow melts the chocolate onto the graham crackers. Every will want "Some More."

title: sauerbraten
directions: Marinate meat in vinegar, water, bay leaves, cloves, salt and pepper for 3 to 5 days.
Then remove meat and brown on both sides. Add 1 1/2 cups vinegar-water and roast in oven at 325°.
Also add carrots and onions and roast about 3 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, add sugar, Pet milk, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla. Mix until blended. Pour into a gallon size ice cream freezer and finish filling container with plain milk. Freeze and serve at once. Fruits can be added if desired.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; set aside.
Mix the milk, eggs and vanilla in separate bowl.
Mix the flour, soda and sugar in a separate bowl.
Mix all together.
Pour in greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: orange "stuff"
directions: Cook these 3 ingredients with 2 3/4 cups water.
Cool.
Add 2 small cans drained mandarin oranges and 1 (8 ounce) container of Cool Whip.

title: basic bouillon gravy
directions: Whisk cornstarch or flour into cool bouillon; season to taste. Heat until mixture becomes thickened; serve.
Yields 3 cups.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and pour chocolate over.
Mix until all ingredients are coated.
Spread on wax paper lined cookie sheets.
Put in refrigerator until chocolate hardens.
Break up into bite-size pieces.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and peanut butter until smooth.
Mix flour and oats together. Add peanut butter mixture to flour and oat mixture.
Stir until moistened. Spread in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Pat in pan. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown. Don't overcook.
Cool before frosting.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Put in muffin pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: full of balony(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 30 seconds or until cheese melts.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put peppers through grinder or food processor.
Pour boiling water over them after they are ground and drained.
Make syrup from vinegar, sugar and salt. Add the veggies and bring to a boil. Simmer until a little thick.
Pour into jars.

title: cheddar-chive ham biscuits with plum jam
directions: Make biscuits.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease large baking sheet.
In large bowl mix flour, baking powder, salt and cayenne. Add butter.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissors fashion, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add cheese and chives; mix.
Stir in enough milk to form soft dough. Turn out onto lightly floured surface; knead 2 to 3 times.
Pat to 1/2-inch thickness.
With 1 1/2-inch round floured biscuit cutter, cut out biscuits.
Reroll scraps and cut.
Place on baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes and cool.
While biscuits bake, make jam.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bone.
Cut into pieces.
Set aside.
Put 1/2 cup of chow mein noodles in greased casserole dish (may need 2) combine everything else.
Sprinkle reserved noodles on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party rye pizza
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger together; drain.
Add cheese and seasoning; stir over low heat until melted.
Spread on bread, then broil until toasted.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in a stick of butter.
Wash rice and combine in medium casserole dish with soups.
Cook 1 hour.
May add almond slices on top in the last 10 minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add salt, baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Stir in oats, flour and coconut.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: russian cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onions finely.
Add sugar.

title: squash patties
directions: Mash drained squash.
Combine all the ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil in a large skillet.
Flatten patties to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cook until golden brown.
Turn and brown on the other side.

title: peanut butter cornflakes cookies
directions: Boil sugar and white syrup up one time.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and cornflakes.
Pour in slightly greased pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: almonilla riveria fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix together sugar, milk and butter. Cook slowly without stirring until mixture reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove pan from heat; add filberts and flavorings.
Stir until mixture cools.
Pour into a shallow buttered pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Cut into pieces.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, celery and bell pepper in butter.
Remove from skillet.
Cut sausage in 1/4-inch rounds and brown on both sides.
Return sauteed vegetables to pan.
Add beans, tomatoes and all other ingredients.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix good and pour over packed pickles in gallon jar.
No cooking, so make sure sugar is dissolved and solution is mixed well.
Sliced onion may be used, 2 or 3.
Pimentos can be added, if desired.
Store in refrigerator for at least 10 days before using.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Slice 1-inch off top of cake; set aside.
Cut down into cake, removing interior, leaving a wall 1-inch thick on all sides. Place cake on plate.
In medium saucepan, combine marshmallows, water and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly on low heat until marshmallows melt; add chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Cool to room temperature.
Whip 1 cup whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spoon mixture into hollowed portion of cake.
Replace top of cake.
Frost with additional whipped cream or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon color.
Beat in sugar slowly. Fold in sifted dry ingredients.
Add all at once.
Put butter and milk in saucepan and bring to a simmering point.
Pour over egg mixture and mix well.
Turn into greased 7-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato onion supreme
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Set aside. Place onions, water and bouillon in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until onions are tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine cheese and sour cream.
In a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish, layer half the potatoes, onions and cheese mixture. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Top potato mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes until heated through.
Garnish with chopped fresh parsley and several onion rings.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cream of barley soup
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 to 5 hours.
Remove ham hock and bay leaf; discard.
Add potatoes. Mix milk slowly into flour and add to soup (or omit milk and flour and add 1/2 cup cream).
Cook on high for 15 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: chilly orange drink
directions: Pour 1/4 cup of orange drink into each glass.
Next put half of the sherbet into each glass.
Finally add half of the ginger ale to each glass.
Drink up! Makes 2 drinks.

title: shrimp mold
directions: In large saucepan, bring undiluted soup to a boil. Dissolve gelatine in cold water. Add mixture to hot tomato soup. Add cream cheese; beat with an egg beater or wire whisk. Let cool. Add celery, onion, mayonnaise and cut up shrimp. Spread mold with mayonnaise. Pour mixture into mold. Chill for 24 hours. Loosen with warm water over mold. Invert on lettuce leaves on a platter. (Fits perfectly into 5 1/2-cup fish mold.) Serve with Escort crackers or Wheat Thins. Appetizer for 12 people or more.

title: gooey chewy cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until lightly browned. Cool and cut into bars.

title: hot sausage appetizer
directions: Fry sausage.
Thoroughly combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These can be prepared ahead and frozen.
Put back in oven in heavy duty Reynolds Wrap at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat milk, marshmallows and candy in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows and candy are melted and blended.
Refrigerate about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped by spoon.
Beat whipping cream in chilled large bowl with electric mixer on high speed until soft peaks form.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate, uncovered, for at least 8 hours or until set.	Garnish with sliced strawberries.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In a 4-quart pan, gently melt oleo.
Add onions, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until softened.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and chicken broth.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add seasonings, chicken, ham and okra.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over fluffy white rice.

title: caramel pudding(also called velvet or milk pudding)
directions: Place mold over low heat with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bring sugar to caramel stage.
Coat mold and cool.
Beat eggs well; add milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour mixture in mold and bake in a preheated 300° oven for about 1 hour or when moving mold around, pudding is solid in the center.
Cool and take out of mold.
Do not overbake.

title: corn flake crunchies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add the egg, milk and grated orange peel and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture.
Add chopped nuts and corn flakes and mix well.

title: three day coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, pepper and pimento.
Set aside. Combine other ingredients and bring to a hard boil.
Pour hot sauce over chopped vegetables and mix well.
Pack into containers and cover.
Let set in refrigerator for 3 days without removing cover.
Yields 12 servings.

title: angel rolls(no rising necessary)
directions: *I have used self-rising flour with good results.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In large skillet, brown chicken and garlic in 3 tablespoons oil.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add pasta sauce, then chicken; stir. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, adding peppers during last 5 minutes. Uncover; top each chicken breast with half cheese slice.
Toss hot cooked macaroni with last tablespoon oil and parsley.
Serve with chicken and sauce.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: party taco dip(appetizer)
directions: Heated:
Brown the ground beef and prepare as directed on taco seasoning package.
Spread taco meat on a cookie sheet or platter. Spread refried beans on top of beef.
(Can be heated now or reheated in oven prior to adding cold items.)

title: italian cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, milk, vanilla, lemon juice and baking powder, then add flour.
If batter seems to be sticky, add a little more flour.
Make strips of pastry, about 2-inches wide.
Bake about 15 minutes on a greased cookie sheet at 375° (strips will not be brown).
Frost when cool and cut diagonally.
Cake decorations can be sprinkled over the frosting before cutting.
Store cookies in airtight containers.
They will keep fresh for weeks.

title: vinegar chess pie
directions: Melt oleo and mix with all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry salad
directions: Drain strawberries.
Measure syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth. Chill about 20 minutes.
Fold in strawberries.
Chill until firm (at least 2 hours).
Garnish with whip cream.

title: baked corn
directions: Place corn in 2-quart casserole.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add to the milk with the eggs.
Pour over the corn; dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad *
directions: Add broccoli to boiling water.
Cook 3 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
Pour into large bowl. Combine vinegar, oil, sugar and salt in small bowl.
Beat with wire whisk.
Pour dressing over broccoli; toss well and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oven french fries "lite"
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into long strips, 1/2-inch wide.
Dry strips thoroughly on paper towels.
Toss in bowl with oil as if tossing a salad.
Sprinkle in herbs or seasonings.
When strips are coated, spread them in single layers on cookie sheet.
Place in oven at 475° for 35 minutes.
Turn strips occasionally to brown on all sides.
If you want strips crisper, brown for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 6.
Per serving:
80 calories.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat together cake mix and oil; then add eggs.
Next add jello dissolved in the water; do not underbeat.
Last of all beat in the strawberries.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tidbits
directions: Melt oleo and grease; mix in sauce and salts.
Put dry ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Pour liquid mixture over dry ingredients and mix so that liquid is coated over all.
Roast in oven for 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Do not cover. Store in tight containers.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn on cookie sheet that has been greased.
Boil margarine, sugar, syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 teaspoon soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to juice to make 1 cup. Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over gelatin.
Add 1/3 cup cold water.
Stir and set aside.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cover zucchini with boiling water.
Allow to set 5 minutes. Drain and put in pastry lined pie pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugar, salt, flour and lemon juice and pour over zucchini.
Dot with margarine and cover with top crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Line greased baking dish with pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix crushed crackers, sugar and flour.
Cover the cheese. Melt butter and add pineapple juice.
Pour over top of mixture. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: frosty strawberry "cupcakes"
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Pour into 12 foil or paper-lined muffin cups.
Freeze until solid.
Thaw at least 15 minutes before serving.

title: molasses cake
directions: Stir together and bake in thin layer at 375° until done.
Make 6 layers.
Stack with cooked, mashed, dried sweetened apples, applesauce or apple butter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or less.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, then pour over apples and stir. Add sugar and mix. In a separate bowl, sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add that to first mixture, then add walnuts and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Bake 1 hour at 350° (metal pan) or 300° (glass pan) in a 13 x 9 pan that is greased and floured. When cooled, sift confectioners sugar on top.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and form into bite-size meatballs.

title: quick sweet pickles
directions: Partially
precook vegetables, if desired.
(Juice will be clearer
if carrots and celery are precooked in salt water for
a minute
or two).
Spear garlic on wooden pick for easy removal. In
a large bowl or crock combine vegetables, garlic and
salt. Cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add soups and enchilada sauce.
In a greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch), layer meat, tortillas and cheese.
Repeat layers until all is used.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add anything needed to taste; add more jalapenos for better salsa.
Keeps 1 to 2 weeks in refrigerator (the older it gets, the hotter it gets).

title: big mac sauce
directions: Blend with fork and refrigerate.

title: grape butter
directions: Cook 20 minutes.
Put through colander to remove seeds.
Seal with paraffin.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir several times to mix.
This recipe can be cut in half.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until creamy.
Sift in flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; stir.
Add vanilla and remaining ingredients.
Turn into a greased and well-floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Cool in pan before turning out.

title: oklahoma slaw
directions: Mix cut vegetables and sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top.
Bring all other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Seal in closed container and refrigerate.
Marinate at least overnight. Serves 8-10.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in double boiler.
Mix peanut butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Pour in melted chips and margarine along with 4 tablespoons of milk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Beat together.
Press into pan and place in refrigerator until firm.
Cut and serve.

title: homemade ice cream(van doren hotel, holly springs, mississippi)
directions: Scald milk.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add 1 tablespoon flour; beat well.
Put a little of the hot milk into the egg and flour mixture.
Mix well, then add this mixture to the scalded milk. Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and freeze in 2-gallon freezer.

title: cabbage, rice and hamburger casserole
directions: Place cabbage in 2-quart casserole (Pam sprayed).
Sprinkle rice over cabbage. Brown and separate hamburger in skillet. Drain. Place hamburger over rice.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of first 6 ingredients.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Use half of the potatoes, onion and sauce, then repeat the layer.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour. Uncover and continue baking until brown.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Mix the cream cheese, salad dressing and Ranch dressing. Spread 2 tubes of crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
After crust is cooled, add the cream cheese mixture and add your veggies, tomatoes, peppers, onions, broccoli, olives, cauliflower, etc.

title: nancy's crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften butter to room temperature. Knead into flour.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix in pecans.
Using a scoop or hands, form into small balls; place on cookie sheets. Bake about 45 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot. Let cool and re-roll in sugar.
Makes about five dozen crescents.

title: joy's caramel icing
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in brown sugar; cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk; continue to stir until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.

title: scallop stew
directions: Saute onions, sprinkled with garlic, in butter.
Remove from pan.
Saute scallops in same butter, sprinkled with Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Mix onion, scallops and two milks and heat slowly.
Add pepper and a pat of butter.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mash coarsely the sweet potatoes and blend with the rest of the dry ingredients.

Lightly mix dry ingredients with buttermilk, stirring with a spoon. Sweet potatoes can be moist or dry so adjust the amount of buttermilk to form a smooth dough. Spread the biscuit dough out 1/2-inch thick on a floured counter. Cut and bake in a 400° oven until well browned, about 15 minutes.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour 2 c. batter into greased 13 x 9 in. baking pan, bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt caramels and margarine with Eagle Brand milk, stirring until smooth. Spread evenly over cake, spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture. Top with pecans. Return to oven; bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Cool. Garnish as desired.

title: cheese and bacon pie
directions: Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 30 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lasagna with uncooked noodles
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and add spaghetti sauce combined with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Best if made two days in advance.
For spicier salsa, use more medium or hot taco sauce. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broiled tato-skins
directions: Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop out insides. Spread inside of shell with melted margarine and sprinkle with salt.
Sprinkle each half with cheese and bacon.
Broil in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with dollop of sour cream and green onion.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add soups, cheese, pimientos, chicken, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Place berries in pie shell.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and sour cream until well blended; pour over berries.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken into melted butter and roll in dry ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Easy, but delicious.

title: beef baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In large mixing bowl mix all ingredients and pour into large baking dish.
Cover with bacon slices.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir into sugar, oil, egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well. Bake in a round 2 1/2 x 10-inch tube pan or 4 x 12-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat carrot apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with cooking spray (canola is best). Combine all cake ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat until well mixed.

Pour into prepared pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center of cake. Cool completely. Serve with a small scoop of low-fat frozen vanilla yogurt or spoon a little of the Fat-Free Dessert Sauce over top just before serving. Best made a day or two before serving.

title: candied carrots(serves 4)
directions: Scrap carrots and slice crosswise on bias, about 1/2 inch thick.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling water, until just tender, 6 to 10 minutes.

title: cajun chicken breasts
directions: In a glass bowl mix all ingredients together.
In the same bowl spread mixture over chicken breasts, then cover, and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
With little vegetable oil fry it in a skillet for 3 to 5 minutes per side or until nicely browned.
Serve over spiced rice.

title: white bean soup
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until golden.
Add oregano, rosemary and sage.
Cook 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and white beans. Simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornstarch in crock-pot.
Cook all day.
Add cornstarch when ready to serve to thicken.
May need to add more water depending on size of crock-pot.
Very good with venison.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: In a saucepan, mix pie filling, sugar, Jell-O, orange juice and pineapple.
Stir, while heating, until hot, not boiling. Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour into mold or other container. Refrigerate.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together the first 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and the egg.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fill a 12-cup greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Remove muffins from oven; immediately dip muffins in melted butter or margarine, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture until coated.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: easy munchie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix cake mix, oil and eggs. Fold in raisins and walnuts. Spoon on cookie sheet. Cook 8 to 10 minutes, until done. Cool. Yields 24 to 36.

title: peanut pudding pie
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Press in 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2/3 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of margarine.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Mix together spaghetti, spaghetti sauce and hamburger.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add cheese. Melt cheese and then add pepperoni.
Ready to serve.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread the pineapple, then the cherries and sprinkle the cake mix on top of the fruit.
Put pecans on top of that and dot with the butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook cornbread as directed on package.
When cornbread is done, crumble in a bowl and add onions, celery, bell peppers, eggs and sage.
Mix and stir well.
Mash all cornbread clumps.
Add all soups.
Mix extremely even.
Add chicken broth.
Let stand to absorb.
Repeat until cake mix like batter (thick and creamy). Must remain loose.
Add cooked chicken and pour into greased pan and cook at 400° until veggies are tender and top is brown, usually 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves approximately 25.

title: herbed potato wedges(serves 2)
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the Parmesan cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Brush the cut sides of the potato wedges with the oil, and dip into the cheese mixture.
Place wedges in a greased 8 inch square pan and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20-25 minutes, or until tender.

title: chicken and ham casserole
directions: Boil chicken; take meat off bones and chop up.
Put chicken and ham in baking dish.
Mix soup, milk, onions, green pepper and celery together and cook until boiling.
Thicken if needed.
Pour over chicken and ham.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake until cracker crumbs are brown.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cherries.
Make a ball. Form into a log.
Make a trench in log and line with cherries. Chill in refrigerator; slice to serve.
Can be wrapped in foil and refrigerated or frozen for up to 6 months.

title: halloween popcorn balls
directions: Combine Alaga syrup, sugar, vinegar and salt in a saucepan. Heat to a boil over a medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture reaches 260° on a candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a hard ball). Reduce heat to low.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, mix and shape into large balls.
Makes 12 balls.

title: mocha oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over instant coffee.
Stir in quick oats, cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat together.
Add to oat mixture the margarine and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs to oat mixture.
Stir in sifted mixture of flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: jif easter nests
directions: In large mixing bowl, use your hands to break noodles into smaller pieces. In large saucepan, combine sugar and syrup. Cook over medium heat until sugar is melted and edges begin to bubble. Add Jif peanut butter and stir until smooth. Pour mixture over noodles and toss to coat. Carefully test for temperature. With slightly buttered hands, form mixture into tight balls using approximately 1/4 cup mixture per ball. Make indentation in center of each ball to resemble a bird's nest. Place on waxed paper and allow to cool completely. Place 2 or 3 jelly beans or candies into each nest. Makes approximately 1 dozen.

title: southern coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: almond bars
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and almond extract.
Beat again until fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or a jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: roast beef repose
directions: Have rib roast at room temperature; season as you like. Preheat oven to 375°.
Place rib side down in pan.
Put into oven for 1 hour, then turn off heat.
Do not open door.
Forty minutes before you wish to serve the roast, turn oven on to 375° and let roast get piping hot.
Takes about 40 minutes.
Roast will be rare and juicy, if more doneness is desired, cook for 55 to 60 minutes more.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Into a large pot, place and mix milk, rice and sugar.
Bring to a boil; lower to medium heat.
Let simmer until most of liquid is absorbed (about 45 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
When done, slightly beat 3 eggs in a small bowl; add some hot mixture and mix.
Add the egg mixture to the milk mixture.
Cook 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Mix. Pour into an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Dust with cinnamon. Serve cold.

title: easy spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, beef and rice. Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: delicious fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, stir well and pour into greased pans. Since no cooking is required, this fudge is foolproof and stays creamy indefinitely.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix all together.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle clean towel with powdered sugar, then sprinkle top of cake.
Tip cake onto towel and roll tightly right away and refrigerate until almost cool.
Unroll and spread with filling.

title: hidden valley potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (thin).
Melt margarine and toss potatoes to coat.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Sprinkle with dressing.
Toss and coat well.

title: diet jello
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water to Kool-Aid and sweetener.
Mix all together and add 2 1/2 cups cold water.

title: snow cherries
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water. Cool. Stir in cherry pie filling. Refrigerate for one hour. Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip. Fold into Jell-O mixture and place in a decorative mold.

title: turtle brownies
directions: *Suggestions:
Pillsbury with walnuts, double fudge brownies or your favorite recipe.

title: english muffins
directions: Place raisins, water and oil in large mixing bowl.
Stir in salt, sugar, milk, oatmeal and wheat germ and gradually add flours. Grease and cover dough.
Allow to double in bulk.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Cut with a 3-inch round cookie cutter. Place on a floured surface to rise.

title: fish fillets with crab meat sauce
directions: Saute onions in oleo until soft.
Add flour and smooth into oleo.
Do not brown.
Add milk, stirring to prevent lumping.
Add sour cream and crab meat.
Remove from heat.
Brush fillets with oleo and place on greased sheet pan.
Spoon equal amount of crab meat sauce on each fillet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley, lemon and paprika.

title: grandma's blanc mange
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk (I use a whisk).
Heat to boiling, then boil gently for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into mold which has been rinsed in cold water.
Chill.
Serve with cream or crushed fruit.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar; add flour.
Roll out thin.
Use cookie cutters.
Wet top of cookie with egg white and sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes or golden brown.

title: rice pudding custard type
directions: Add all ingredients. Bake in oven and dot with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Set pan of water in oven while baking. Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Check with knife.
When knife comes out clean, it's done.

title: lemon pilaf
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add lemon juice, rice and seasoning.
Toss lightly.
Serve with broiled chicken or fish.

title: easy cranberry crisp
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oats, flour, brown sugar and melted butter; stir until well blended.
Spread half of dry mixture in greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Cover with cranberry sauce.
Top with remaining dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares and serve warm with ice cream.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: linguine with tomato basil sauce(a quick, healthy recipe loved by kids and adults)
directions: Heat oil in a saucepan.
Add tomatoes, garlic, salt, pepper and basil. Cook for 5 minutes over moderate heat.
Cook linguine. Drain and pour sauce over linguine.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: "souper-burgers"
directions: In skillet, brown chuck and onion in shortening.
Stir to separate meat.
Add vegetable soup, ketchup, mustard and pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.
Garnish with onion and tomato slices.

title: good fruit cocktail
directions: Drain fruit; add water to equal 3 cups.
Add to pudding.
Cook until thick.
Cool; add cherries and bananas.

title: pork roast with dressing and kraut
directions: Put pork roast in large roasting pan.
Cover with water and onion soup.
Put in oven at 200° and cook while you're sleeping. Fix your favorite dressing using the pork broth.
Leave about 1-inch of broth in bottom of pan.
Place meat in middle of pan. Put dressing on one end and drained kraut on the other end.
Bake until dressing is done.
This is easy and tastes great!

title: pie crust
directions: Finish filling cup with water.
Add to other ingredients. Makes 5 crusts.

title: zipped-up dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese, buttermilk and lemon juice until smooth and creamy.
Put in small mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 3/4 cups (13 calories per tablespoon).

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Place in layers in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: pretzel sparklers
directions: Dip the pretzel rod halfway into the melted white chocolate then sprinkle the sprinkles, cake decorations or mini M&M's over the wet chocolate. Lay on wax paper or place in a cup to dry.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a Bundt cake mold. *Make sure the pan is sprayed with Pam.

title: broiled salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place on broiler pan.
Broil 5 minutes on each side.
Serve while juicy and hot.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp with rice
directions: Boil rice according to box directions.
Rinse rice so it will not stick together.
In frying pan, fry onions in oil until clear; add shrimp and fry until pink.
Add rice to shrimp mixture; stir until onion and shrimp are evenly distributed through the rice. Add eggs, mixing until they are evenly distributed.
Put cover on pan; reduce heat to low and cook 15 to 20 minutes until eggs set.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Crumble and cook sausage in skillet.
Drain and blend in the cream cheese.
Set aside.
Turn oven on according to directions for crescent rolls.
Unroll the crescent rolls and tear in half to make 4 rectangles by pressing together the perforations.
Spread the sausage and cheese mixture on top and roll up; slice into 5 sections.
Lay them on cookie sheet and bake.
Continue same process for other can of crescent rolls.
Makes 40 Sausage Rolls.

title: jel-cheese salad*
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add enough water to make 1 cup juice.
Cook sugar and pineapple together 5 minutes.
Soak jello in juice until dissolved, then add to hot pineapple-sugar mixture. Stir.
Cool.
Fold in cheese and whipped evaporated milk.
Pour in ice tray.
Place in freeze unit until firm.
Cut in squares. Serve on lettuce.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Melt butter; add to mixture.
Add pecans and chocolate chips, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into 10-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: applesauce muffin mix
directions: Mix applesauce and soda;
set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together
flour and spices.
Add flour, butter mixture and applesauce
and
soda
together;
mix.
Add nuts. Bake at 400° for 20
minutes.
This
dough may be stored in refrigerator 1 to 3 months if stored in an airtight container.

title: date pudding
directions: Put soda on dates and hot water; let stand.
Mix together sugar, egg, salt, baking powder, butter, flour and nuts.
Add dates to this mixture and bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes until soft.
Mash completely. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: coquille sainte jacques
directions: Heat wine; add washed scallops with a pinch of salt.
If bay scallops are unavailable, cut scallops in 2 or 3 pieces.
Simmer about 10 minutes or until scallops turn very white.
Drain and reserve liquid.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add onions, mushrooms, parsley, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper to taste.
When onions and mushrooms are tender, add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add reserved liquid and cream slowly; allow to cook until sauce thickens.
Add scallops and paprika; blend well.

title: three-bean chili
directions: Rinse and drain beans; set aside. In a large pot, cook onion in oil until onion is tender, not brown. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered. Stir occasionally. Top with cheese, sour cream or any toppings of choice.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Make brownies according to directions on box.
While brownies are in the oven, break up peppermint patties into small pieces. As soon as brownies are done, sprinkle peppermint patty pieces evenly over entire pan.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and carefully spread melted candy over brownies.
Cool and cut.

title: peanut butter sandwich
directions: If you still crave
a
peanut butter sandwich, try this one.

title: easy spaghetti bake
directions: Fry bacon about 2 minutes; remove from pan and drain.
Cook onions until soft; add ground beef and garlic powder.
Brown lightly.
Stir in salt, pepper, chili powder, tomato sauce, water and drained bacon.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Break half spaghetti into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes longer, until browned and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions 1/4-inch thick.
Saute onions in butter until tender and spoon into 11 x 7-inch glass dish.
Spread cheese over onions.

title: blueberry salad dessert
directions: Mix together and let set.

title: banana mallow
directions: Fold in 1 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows and 1 cup whipped cream in crust.
Cut up 2 bananas and pour filling in crust. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: layered mexican dip(servings:  10)
directions: To assemble:
Spread bean dip on large, shallow platter.
Top with avocado mixture (mashed avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper, mixed).
Top with sour cream, mixed with taco seasoning mix.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve cold or room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: marvelous marinade
directions: In a small pan, cook garlic in oil.
Remove from heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except the meat and vegetables.
Pour sauce over meat/chicken in covered container.
Marinate meat/chicken 6 hours or overnight.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add orange sherbet and stir until thoroughly mixed. Add other ingredients, folding cream in last. Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on boxes; drain off water and put broccoli in a casserole dish. Add butter (1/2 of the stick), cut in pieces and the cubed cheese. Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.

title: sauce or syrup for biscuits
directions: Cook sugar and milk in saucepan for several minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
This is good left over, just rewarm it.

title: almond punch
directions: Make a syrup with sugar and 4 cups of water.
Cook until thoroughly dissolved.
While hot, add 4 small or 2 large packages of Jell-O.
Add lemon juice, orange juice concentrate, pineapple juice, almond flavoring and 1 gallon water.
Stir well and fill containers 3/4 full.
Freeze.
Defrost about 2 hours.
Use 3 to 4 large bottles of ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: salami
directions: Mix spices and sprinkle in small amounts over meat and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 4 days.
Knead once a day, each day. On the 4th day, knead again and shape into 10 rolls,
1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Bake at 150° for 8 hours, turning once.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: grandma's yogurt pancakes
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat together the yogurt, egg and water and add to dry ingredients gently.
Cook by 1/4 cupfuls on hot greased grill.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry all vegetables in 1/2 cup canola oil.
Season with soy sauce and ginger.
Add meat of your choice.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Stir-fry about 20 minutes.
Delicious served with rice, sweet and sour sauce, hot mustard and crackers!

title: spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 1/2 cups water 10 minutes.
Add Crisco and let cool.
Then add sifted dry ingredients to this.
Beat eggs thoroughly and add them to other mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fabulous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal and blend in a blender to a fine powder and set aside.	Place chocolate bar in blender and chop into very small pieces and set aside.
Cream the butter and the two sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chocolate chips, chopped chocolate bar and nuts; mix well.
This is a stiff cookie dough. Roll into balls and place two-inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Cookies will be soft to the touch, but they will become more firm when cool.
Store in tight container.

title: beef and shrimp stir-fry
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin slices; coat with 1 tablespoon stir-fry sauce.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Remove and cut broccoli flowerets into bite size pieces.
Peel stems; cut diagonally into thin slices.

title: flounder fillet
directions: I like plenty.
In a foil-lined pan, arrange fillets in a single layer.
Sprinkle the juice from the lime over the fish. With a fork, whisk together mayonnaise, Parmesan and scallions; spread over fillets.
Broil about 6 inches from high heat until fish is opaque when flaked with a fork and topping is golden, about 6 minutes.
Remove fillets to hot dinner plates and serve at once. Serves six.

title: coconut cake
directions: Blend cake
mix,
pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing
bowl.
Beat
with electric mixer at medium speed for 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with Coconut Cream Cheese Icing.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken in baking dish.
Marinate several hours.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about an hour.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes in cream of tartar and water; drain.
Put half of ham, potatoes and onion in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hour or on high for 4 hours.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, milk, cream of tartar, baking soda, vanilla and flour.
Grease and flour cookie sheet. Drop 1 teaspoon at a time.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Don't bake too long! Makes about 6 dozen.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Mix wet and dry ingredients separately, then add both to eggs and mix until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix well eggs, sugar, flour, soda and pumpkin pie spice and fold in canned pumpkin and lemon juice.
Grease large cookie sheet, then spread mix on it.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll like a jelly roll in a damp towel.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to first bowl and stir only until blended.
Spoon into well-greased or paper lined muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for one minute and remove from pan.

title: chocolate zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in sugar and oil.
Stir chocolate into egg mixture along with zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
With a large spoon, stir into zucchini mixture along with nuts and chips.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into two well-greased 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch pan, the pretzel sticks, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Cover bottom of pan and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix pizza sauce and put in dish.
Add pepperoni and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add crescent rolls and bake 10 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Heat oil in heavy metal pan to 375°.
Slice a large onion crosswise, about 3/8-inches thick.
Separate into rings.
Dip rings first in buttermilk, then flour.
Repeat this 3 times.
Fry in oil (turning once) until golden brown.
Use tongs to put in and remove.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm in 200° oven until serving.
Season as desired with salt.

title: hearty winter stew
directions: Cut beef cubes into bite-sized pieces.
Peel potatoes and dice. Cut up onions.
Cut up whole tomatoes (save juice).
Coat bottom of soup pot with oil.
Place beef cubes and onions into pot.
Brown, drain off excess fat.
Add saved juice, tomato sauce, potatoes, tomatoes and all frozen vegetables to pot.
Fill pot to top with water.
Simmer for 3 to 4 hours on top of stove.
Serve with rolls and butter.

title: cold carrots
directions: Slice carrots; boil in salted water until tender; let cool. Add sliced onions to carrots.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and pour over carrots and onions.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast casserole(company)
directions: Brown pork links.
Brown bacon and drain and crumble.
Beat eggs.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Spray or butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange bread slices in bottom.
Spread meat and mushrooms over it. Add milk and egg mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chinese supper
directions: Heat everything, but soy sauce, in large frypan.
Top with soy sauce to taste.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine milk, eggs and oil, then mix with dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased cornstick pan for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
If baked as cornbread or muffins, cook longer.

title: chili with corn meal dumplings
directions: Prep: 15 minutes. Cook: 20 minutes. Bake: 40 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and vinegar until it stands between the prongs of a fork.
Pour half gradually into well beaten whites. Let the rest cook a little longer, then pour it in gradually and beat thoroughly.
Add nuts and drop.

title: irish stew
directions: Heat a pan with oil.
Saute meat until well done.
You may have to cook meat in 3 separate batches.
Remove meat.
Using same oil, saute onions for 8 minutes.
Add meat back to pan.
Pour beer and beef stock in; cover.
Let cook for 1 hour on low heat.
Add vegetables; cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mother's rice pudding
directions: Make Minute rice according to package directions for 6 servings.
Add milk and sugar.
Stir well; heat until just before boiling.
To egg yolks add the vanilla.
Gradually add egg mixture to rice mixture as not to curdle egg.
Stir well.
Pour into a 3-quart bowl.

title: honey cake
directions: Blend together oil, sugar and egg yolks; add honey.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice, ginger and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture alternately with coffee.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Pour into lightly greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In medium skillet, prepare ground beef, taco mix and water according to package. Add refried beans and heat 5 minutes. In one-quart casserole dish, spread beef and bean mixture. Layer remaining ingredients in order given. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Chop spinach in food processor.
Do not puree!
Saute chopped onion in butter until soft.
Add spinach.
Slowly add cream, white pepper and dash of nutmeg.
Heat until hot.

title: ham and cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate. Good for finger sandwiches.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, bring to boil, remove from heat and add soup and oil.
Shake well.
After bottling and before use, refrigerate.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Blend cashew nuts and water together until smooth.
Pour into pot with salt, tomato puree, water, onion powder and honey.
Heat (simmer) until thickened.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Stir ice cream and Cool Whip together.
Crumble cookies and add them to ice cream. Freeze.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Bake 10 to 13 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Melt yeast in water; melt shortening.
Put egg in bowl; beat. Add sugar and salt.
After yeast has melted in water, pour into mixture.
Add flour, stirring to mix well.
Let rise and then make into rolls.
Let rise again and bake in hot oven at about 400° until golden brown.
May be stored in refrigerator, if desired.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Combine first four ingredients, mixing well.
Drain and chop oysters.
Stir olives and oysters into cream cheese mixture. Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl combine cake mix, eggs, sour cream, Kahlua and vegetable oil.
Using electric mixer, beat at low speed 3 to 5 minutes at medium fast speed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (ovens vary) or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 30 minutes.
Loosen from pan and invert.
Remove pan and cool completely on rack, top side up.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or make glaze with 2 to 3 tablespoons Kahlua and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Drizzle on top.

title: cauliflower, bacon and lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce pieces, onion slices, bacon and cauliflower. Spread mixture of last three items as dressing on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter and eggs in saucepan until thickened. Stir constantly 12 minutes.
Add vanilla, pecans and coconut. Frost the top of cake, not sides.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt chocolate and butter together. Allow to cool slightly.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla and butter flavoring in a large bowl.
Add the melted chocolate/butter mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook meat in a large skillet; drain. Add remaining ingredients.

title: grandma brown's peach cobbler
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and milk in blender.
Blend and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Add peaches.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yield:
8 servings.
I put peaches on the bottom.

title: crab cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on wheat crackers.
This is always a big hit and is a nice appetizer.
It is even good on a baked potato.

title: western style frittata
directions: In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat 2 tablespoons butter over low heat; add bacon and cook.
Add onions and green pepper, stirring frequently; cook about 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, cheese, pepper and bacon mixture until combined.
Melt 2 more tablespoons butter; add to egg mixture.
Cook on low heat until bottom is set.
Place in a preheated 300° oven.
Cook until desired consistency is reached, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing and spread on top of salad. Cover with plastic wrap.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Sprinkle 1 small package of instant lemon pudding mix over fruit and liquid.
Mix and let stand.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix all ingredients together to taste. Refrigerate overnight.

title: brandied carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 2 1/2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Place carrots in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over carrots.
Cover and cook in a 375° oven until carrots are tender, about 40 minutes.

title: black bottom goodies
directions: Combine first flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and cocoa in a large bowl. Make a well in center of mixture. Combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla and add to dry ingredients. Stir well. Spoon batter into paper-lined miniature muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Combine cream cheese, egg, 1/2 cup sugar and salt, stirring well. Stir in chocolate morsels. Spoon about 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: caponatina(sicilian style)
directions: Peel and dice eggplant and fry in 1 cup hot olive oil.
Remove fried eggplant from skillet.
Add remaining oil and onions; brown gently.
Add tomato sauce and celery; cook until celery is tender, adding a little water if necessary.
Add capers, olives, pine nuts and fried eggplant.
Heat vinegar in a small saucepan. Dissolve sugar in vinegar and pour over eggplant.
Add salt and pepper; simmer 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool before serving.

title: noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out on a well-floured board until you have a thin sheet.
Sprinkle well with flour and cut into thin strips.
Let stand 15 minutes and then drop into hot meat juice.
Stir well, then cover.
Cook until done, about 20 minutes or let dry on floured board and place in a bag and store in refrigerator or freezer until ready to use.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter and add 2 eggs to cake mix.
Mix will be sticky, but mix well.
Put in greased sheet cake pan.
Grease only bottom of pan.
Pour pie filling on top of unbaked cake.
Take 2 tablespoons melted butter and mix with frosting.
Sprinkle over entire cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: Melt chocolate and sugar in double boiler; set aside.
Beat yolks.
Beat whites until stiff.
Add yolks, salt, 1 1/2 cups of whipped cream and beaten egg whites to chocolate mixture.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into torte pan lined with ladyfingers.
Add more ladyfingers, then add remaining mixture.
Top with remaining whipped cream.
Chill well.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Add meat and let set 2 hours at room temperature.

title: fruit dip
directions: Using a wire whisk or electric mixer, cream together all ingredients until light and fluffy.
Cut the top 2 inches off a pineapple and scoop out the inside.
Use the pineapple hull as a container for the dip.
Arrange the pineapple, apple slices, strawberries, grapes or any fruit around the dip.
Sprinkle the fruit with Fruit-Fresh to prevent it from turning brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with soup and seasonings.
Stir in about 1/2 of the onion rings.
Pour into casserole and top with grated cheese and remainder of the onion rings.
Bake.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: chow-chow
directions: Grind peppers, onions, cabbage and tomatoes.
Add salt and let stand 2 or 3 hours.
Pour off juice.

title: beef and dill casserole
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion in pan.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce and dill and simmer.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green pepper and scallions.
Place 1/2 noodles in bottom of a greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese mixture, then remaining noodles.
Pour meat mixture over and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix sugar and flour. Add butter and yeast mixture.
Mix and cut out.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes about 12 rolls.

title: pennsylvania dutch beets and pickled eggs
directions: Boil beets for 10 minutes in sugar, water, vinegar and spices. Boil eggs until hard-boiled and shell while still hot.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place all ingredients in blender on high speed.
Add 4 tablespoons olive oil and blend 5 minutes.
Add, do not blend 2 teaspoons chopped chives.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with garlic croutons or diced green pepper or diced black olives or diced cucumber as garnish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Tear apart crescent rolls; fill with chicken and cheese.
Roll up and seal.
Place in a pan.
Mix soup with 1 can of water; pour this over rolls.*
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: oven baked stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large roasting pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 3 hours at 325° or 4 hours at 250°.
(No looking, wait 2 hours, then re-cover and finish baking.)

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients with 1/2 of the pineapple juice (reserve remaining juice).
Pour mixture over chicken and bake for one hour at 350°. Check during baking for desired thickness.
If necessary, pour remaining juice over chicken.

title: crisp white sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Sift 3 times with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Combine eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in fridge overnight.
Turn out on lightly floured board and roll out.
Then cut with floured cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are good for Christmas cut-outs.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: easy casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Stir soup and milk together in the casserole.
Add remaining ingredients except the eggs and mix well. Fold in eggs gently.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels with water and margarine in covered double boiler or in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir occasionally until smooth.
Combine sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add caramel sauce; mix well.
Stir in pecan halves.
Pour into pastry shell; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pie filling will appear to be very soft, but becomes firm as it cools.

title: christmas finger jello
directions: Layer 1:
Mix 1 box Jell-O and 1 package gelatine with 1 cup boiling water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and put into the refrigerator to set, about 20 minutes.

title: meat sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Is very good over meat loaf.

title: stuffed orange roughy
directions: Rinse and pat dry fish fillets.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, if desired.
Arrange fish in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper. Add enough milk to come to top edge of fish.
Sprinkle dry stuffing mix on each fillet.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle paprika on fish.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: In a
pan
over
medium
heat, add the honey and peanut butter.
Stir
until peanut butter melts. Add the cereal.
Mix until well	coated.
Pour
into a long baking dish.
Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl blend cake mix with eggs, water, shortening and oats.
Fold in bananas, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mother's chicken and dressing
directions: Use half biscuit and half cornbread crumbs to thicken broth from chicken.
Add onion, chopped fine.
Add eggs, well beaten and salt, pepper and sage, as desired.
Add margarine.
Cook on top of stove, stirring constantly until margarine is melted, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Mixture will thicken as it cooks.
Add enough evaporated milk to make mixture into thick-pouring consistency. Pour into large baking pan with layers, half of dressing, then chicken and top with remaining dressing.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.
