(I prefer to skin and debone chicken.)

title: no mix bars
directions: Melt margarine
in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add crushed graham crackers, then other ingredients in the order listed.
No, stirring, no bowls and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: baked hash browns
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt butter and combine with cornflakes.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake in 350°
oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cabbage and celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in 3 tablespoons butter 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add cabbage and cook 10 minutes longer.
Pour into greased baking dish; add salt, pepper, white sauce and pimiento. Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Dot with remaining butter and bake in moderate oven at 350°, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into a regular unbaked crust. Cook 10 minutes at 400°, then turn down to 350°. Bake 30 minutes. Cook exact time.

title: salsa
directions: Fry jalapeno pepper in hot oil (best if olive oil is used). Peel and dice.
Dice tomatoes, onions; set aside.
Cut up cilantro down to the stems.
Mix jalapenos, tomatoes, onions, cilantro, garlic and salt until well mixed.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix all together and chill for one hour before serving.
It goes fast; I always make a double batch.

title: pollo con pico de gallo
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and pat dry.
Place in a large plastic bag.
Combine teriyaki sauce, lime peel, juice and garlic.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 hour or longer.
Reserving marinade, remove chicken and grill until done, turning and basting with the marinade, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place on bed of lettuce and serve with Pico De Gallo and warm tortillas.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together.
Mix all ingredients except Hershey's Kisses together.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Then add Hershey's Kisses and bake 2 to 5 minutes more.

title: chocolate pecan squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup margarine and 2 ounces chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir in graham cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans. Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan; chill 30 minutes.

title: waldorf chicken salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and serve on a bed of lettuce or in fresh croissants.

title: crisp noodle chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in a single layer in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In a bowl, combine soup, sour cream, soup mix and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: oat bran fruit muffins(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin tin with paper liners.
In a large bowl mix oat bran, flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and dried fruits.
In another bowl, mix brown sugar, buttermilk, honey, oil and eggs.
Make a well in dry ingredients. Pour liquid mixture into well and stir gently.
Do not overmix. Spoon into paper-lined muffin tin.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 18; 1 muffin per serving.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Start out with 1/4 c. olive oil, then add more if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough ice cubes so that when they melt the soup is not too watery.

title: one cup salad
directions: Mix well. Chill. Best if served after chilled for at least 3 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil until tender; drain. Combine all ingredients and about 2 cups dressing mix or more. Mix together. Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle top with more dressing mix. Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: popovers
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Add the eggs, well beaten and also the milk.
Beat hard with an electric beater for 2 minutes, then pour at once into hot greased muffin pans.
Bake about 25 minutes in a hot oven at 450°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone boiled chicken.
Mix melted margarine and stuffing. Put 1/2 in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Top with diced chicken.
Pour mixture of chicken soup, broth and sour cream over chicken.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing on top.
Spoon 7 to 8 tablespoons of broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: round steak with beer marinade
directions: In a one gallon jar, combine the beer, scallions, oil, green pepper, soy sauce, sugar, garlic, salt and cayenne.
Add steak, turning to coat with marinade, and let it marinate, covered and chilled, turning occasionally for at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake in a 450° oven about 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese cups
directions: Beat these ingredients (except vanilla wafers) together until smooth.
Drop one vanilla wafer on the bottom of a paper lined muffin pan.
Fill muffin cups with 2/3 of cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling and a dab of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 24.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut together salt, sugar,
flour
and shortening.
Stir in water, vinegar and egg with
a fork.
Mix together.
Put in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Makes 5 single crusts.

title: chili pie(appetizer)
directions: In 8-inch pie plate layer the following:
Spread softened cream cheese on bottom.
Spread contents of 1 can chili without beans over cream
cheese.
Sprinkle Velveeta cheese over chili.

title: barbs pudding dessert
directions: In mixing bowl mix pudding, milk, and cool whip; set aside. Line a 13x9-inch pan with a layer of graham crackers.
Add 1/2 of the pudding mixture, add a second layer of graham crackers and the rest of the pudding.
Put a layer of graham crackers then spread the pie filling on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Drain in the morning and add 2 quarts fresh water.
Cook slowly until the skins burst.
Fry bacon or salt pork until crisp.
Add meat and drippings to beans. Add other ingredients and place in a covered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Keep beans covered with liquid while they cook.

title: southern grits casserole
directions: Fry sausage and crumble.
Drain and set aside.
Cut Velveeta into small chunks.
Slowly stir grits into briskly boiling water. When mixture thickens, stir in sausage and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve at once.
Good as supper dish with vegetable, salad and bread.
Serves 4.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut into strips.
Combine oil and all other ingredients in a plastic bag.
Add potatoes; shake to coat. Spread strips in a single layer on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, until tender.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Clean peppers.
Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers, then stand upright in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Bake longer if you want peppers softer.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini or summer squash casserole
directions: Cut unpared squash into bite size pieces.
Lightly cook and drain.
Mix dressing with butter.
Mix all ingredients with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Put in casserole and top with the balance of the dressing.
Bake 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
Can be frozen.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream
sugar and oleo, add egg yolks.
Sift spices with 2 cups flour and add to creamed mixture alternately with fruit juice
and sweet
milk mixture.
Dredge fruit and nuts with 1 cup
flour. Pour
batter
over	dredged fruit and nuts.
Beat egg
whites stiff
and	fold in last.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in double boiler or microwave.
Add horseradish sauce and Miracle Whip.
Blend together.
Add Bac*Os, finely chopped salami or pepperoni according to taste.
Serve with Wheatables.

title: quick fudge
directions: Stir the first 5 ingredients over medium heat until top begins to bubble all over.
Set timer for 5 minutes. Stir.
Add the chocolate pieces, nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan (8-inch square). Set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Can be successfully doubled.
Never fails to harden.

title: easter cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and place in a 9x13 glass dish. Cook in oven
at 400° for 10 mins.
Decrease temperature to 325° and continue to cook for 25-30 mins. until milk curdles (it will look like scrambled eggs when stirred).
Remove from oven and strain mixture. When clear, put into muslin cloth or cheesecloth and drain overnight on counter. Delicious!

title: fresh lumpia
directions: Soak anatto in cooking oil.
Set aside.
Saute garlic in vegetable oil until light brown.
Add onions, pork and shrimp. Pour in soup stock and cover.
Cook over medium heat until pork is tender.
Add sweet potato and potatoes, cook for 5 minutes.
Then mix the rest of vegetables.
Strain atsuete-oil to the vegetable mixture.
Season with salt or fish sauce.
Cook until all vegetables are done.
Add m.s.g.
Cool in a colander while allowing liquid to drain out.

title: coffee breakers
directions: In saucepan melt butter; stir in sugar and syrup, bring to rolling boil.
Spread in large oblong pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Dissolve yeast in warm water in mixing bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and beat vigorously.
Turn dough onto board dusted with Bisquick. Knead until smooth about 20 times.
Roll out into 12-inch square. Brush with melted butter or margarine.
Sprinkle center third with 1/2 the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Fold 1/3 over center third. Sprinkle with remaining sugar-cinnamon.
Fold remaining third over the two layers.
Cut with knife crosswise into strips 1-inch wide. Twist each strip and seal ends.
Place in pan 1 1/2-inches apart. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Invert pan immediately.

title: junk salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients (fruit cocktail may be used instead of pineapple).
Pour into serving dish.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.
Slice layer of bananas on top of salad.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: texas dip
directions: Put Velveeta in crock-pot to melt.
Fry sausage and ground beef until browned.
Add all ingredients except chips to melted cheese and leave in crock-pot on low heat to keep warm until serving time.

title: quick butter cookies
directions: Mix softened margarine and other ingredients with a fork or with fingers.
Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with fork, making crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and desired quantities of chopped onion and green pepper together.
Brown hamburger.
Stir in the tomato sauce.
Boil noodles.
Place 1/2 of the cooked noodles in the bottom of a casserole.
Add a layer of the cheese mixture. Add remaining noodles.
Top with hamburger-tomato sauce mixture. Top with butter as desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandkids' easy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vinegar; mix, then add vanilla.
Mix.
In separate bowl, mix flour and soda.
Mix this mixture with lots of love.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
In large pot, add 2 cans of tomato sauce, vegetables (drained), green beans (drained) and can of potato soup (leftover potatoes or instant potatoes may be used) and ground beef.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Serving for 8.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: mandela's great grandmother's moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add salad dressing, dissolved soda and vanilla.
Put into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° until middle of cake springs back when touched, approximately 34 to 40 minutes baking time.

title: onion casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, place a layer of sliced onions (slices overlapping).
Over this, sprinkle layer of crushed potato chips, then a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat these layers almost to the top of the dish.
Pour soup and milk mixture over all. Bake in moderate oven until onions are tender (about 45 minutes).

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, salt, onion, green pepper, mayonnaise, lemon juice and chicken soup.
Mix well and spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread cheese and potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until heated through and browned.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan. Add onions and parsley. Blend in flour and keep stirring on low heat. Add half and half and cheese; stir until melted. Add salt, pepper and crabmeat. Cook about 10 minutes.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and oil and heat until dissolved. Cool and pour over vegetables.
This salad will keep well for days when stored in the refrigerator.

title: second hand sweet pickles #1
directions: Drain and wash pickles; put in jars.
Cook sugar, vinegar and spices for 5 minutes.
Cool and pour pickles; put cinnamon stick in jar.
Replace lid.

title: chicken spaghetti(serves 12)
directions: Place hen in pan, season with salt and cover with water. Simmer until chicken is ready to take off bone; save broth. While chicken is cooling, place chopped tomatoes in saucepan.
Add onion, green peppers, celery and enough broth from the chicken to prevent sticking.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Debone chicken and cut into bite size pieces.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Combine with chicken, beans, soup, mayonnaise, water chestnuts, onion, pimento, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into a baking dish. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: easy crazy corn
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and then simmer for 2 minutes. Add vanilla and baking soda and stir. Pour mixture over corn and toss until coated. Spread on 2 buttered cookie sheets. Bake at 225° for 30 minutes. Cool on waxed paper and break apart. (Do this as quickly as possible.) Store in airtight container.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes; drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together.

Pour a layer of the sauce in the bottom of baking dish. Season breasts to taste and lay on top of sauce. Cover with remaining sauce. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Put breasts on serving platter and use sauce over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: brown sugar chewies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and margarine.
Mix flour and nuts together in separate bowl before adding to mixture.
Then add to mixture along with vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 45 minutes depending on oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Place chicken pieces in ungreased casserole dish.
In large bowl, combine croutons, celery and onion.
Mix melted butter with 1/4 cup water.
Toss with croutons until liquid is absorbed. Reserve 1 1/2 cups crouton mixture; spread remainder over chicken in casserole.
Blend soup with 1/2 cup water.
Spread over croutons and top with reserved croutons.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Stir flour and salt into butter in a saucepan.
Stir in chicken stock.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Alternate layers of cooked rice, chicken, sauce and vegetables in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
I use a whole chicken.
Cook it with water until it falls apart. Let it cool.
Remove the chicken from the bone and use the juice left in the pan for your chicken stock.
You can put a bouillon cube in the stock for more flavor.
This is your father's favorite.

title: blueberry-orange nut bread
directions: Into mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat together eggs, milk, melted butter or margarine, orange peel and juice; stir into flour mixture just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.
Wrap in foil and store overnight before cutting in slices to serve.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter. Steam broccoli until partially cooked (about 3 minutes); cool and press dry. Beat eggs and milk until frothy. Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into egg mixture, mixing well. Fold in broccoli, cheese and onions. Spoon evenly into the pan. Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake in preheated oven, 350°, for 35 minutes or until set and lightly brown. Let set 5 minutes and cut.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cut up mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks in pieces.
Cut up marshmallows in pieces (use the large marshmallows cut up; they seem to do better and they also melt better into the rest of the salad).
After cutting up the mandarin oranges, pineapple chunks and marshmallows, add some coconut to taste and then add the pint of sour cream.
Let the salad chill and set overnight if possible. The longer the salad sets, the better the flavor.

title: lynn's lemon bars
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar and flour until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Don't cool! Remove promptly.

title: dip(chips or vegetable)
directions: Melt bouillon cube in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Add other ingredients and beat with mixer until well blended.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add sugar, salad oil and eggs; beat well.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut; blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) round layer cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake in moderate oven 35 to 40 minutes. Turn out on wire racks and cool thoroughly.
Fill layers and frost top and sides of cake with cream cheese frosting.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pie filling, sprinkle cake mix, sliced margarine, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Perfect dessert to travel with.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and flour in butter until golden brown.
Add meat mixed with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown well.
Add mushroom soup, bell pepper and pimiento.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream. Heat.
Serve on rice.
Suitable for freezing.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Slice chicken into strips
about
3 inches by 1/4 inch. Combine flour, salt and
pepper in bag.
Add chicken and shake to coat.
In skillet, saute chicken in butter over medium heat until golden and tender.
Remove
to
serving
dish
and
keep warm. Add green onions, mushrooms and wine to skillet.
Cook, stirring until liquid
disappears.
Reduce
heat to low.
Stir in paprika, sour
cream
and
Worcestershire
and
heat
sauce through.
Pour over warm chicken.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, pecans, Grape-Nuts and pineapple with juice.
Crush wafers to make crumbs in an 8-inch square pan.
Make alternate layers of crumbs and pineapple mixture, starting and ending with crumbs.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Cut in squares.
This can be made ahead of time.

title: lemon cake squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix in order the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Place each chicken breast on a sheet of waxed paper; flatten using a meat mallet on rolling pin.
Place 3 to 4 strips of ham across each chicken breast.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese evenly over each chicken breast.
Fold long sides of chicken towards the center; fold in sides of chicken to center, and secure with wooden picks.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until creamy. Put 24 wafers flat side down in paper-lined muffin tins. Put 1 tablespoon of cream cheese mixture over each. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes. They will not brown; do not overbake. Put 1 teaspoon of pie filling on each and refrigerate.

title: london broil
directions: In large glass baking dish combine the Worcestershire sauce, garlic, allspice, thyme and mustard.
Add the meat to the dish and rub the marinade over the surface.
Allow to marinate for 30 minutes.
Broil or grill the meat for about 8 minutes per side for rare.
Carve into thin slices.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips.

title: joe's hominy dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until tender.
Pour off grease. Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Pour in hominy (drained) and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add cumin.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: island sauce salad dressing
directions: Whisk together in saucepan, sugar, flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Gradually add water, egg yolks, vinegar, corn syrup and honey.
Whisk constantly while cooking over low heat about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens, but does not boil.
Take off heat and whisk in corn oil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix ingredients very good; add seasoning to taste.
Use black pepper, seasoning salt, paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, lemon pepper and chopped green onion.

title: myra's lazy day vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in a large covered pot until all vegetables are tender.
I sometimes substitute 1 can cream of chicken for the cream of mushroom soup.

title: pineapple tapioca
directions: Place first four ingredients in top of double boiler and cook over hot water until it is thick (about 1 hour).
Mix with crushed pineapple.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter cornflake balls
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Pour mixture over cornflakes and stir.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and store overnight in refrigerator.
Use as a dip for raw fresh vegetables.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place
slices bread, side by side, in casserole dish (4 slices, buttered side down and 4 slices buttered side up). Mix cheese,
eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Pour
over	bread.	Place sausage on top.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peachy orange yogurt whip
directions: In blender, combine yogurt, juice concentrate, milk and Equal. Add peaches, few at a time.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes, blending until slushy.
Makes 4 (7 ounce) servings.
Diabetic Exchange:
1/2 Milk, 1 Fruit.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until hot.
You can add as many spices as you want.
Use about 1/2 teaspoon of each.

title: mama's pot pie casserole
directions: Mix chicken and vegetables together and place in casserole. Mix soup and broth together and pour over chicken and vegetables. Mix flour and buttermilk together and pour over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container. To serve, mix 1 1/2 tablespoons mixture in mug with boiling water.

title: jiffy lime pie
directions: Note:
This is a super quick dessert for hot summer days and requires no cooking.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: The quantities listed are for 1 skinless, boneless chicken breast.
On foil, mix mayonnaise, mustard and garlic, then spread about size of breast.
Dredge on both sides.
Mix together crumbs, Parmesan, paprika and parsley.
Sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat in Dutch oven.
Add tomato juice, macaroni, tomato paste and chili powder.
Stir and simmer until macaroni is tender.
Water may be added to help mixture stir easily.
Let simmer with lid on for about 15 minutes or longer to help set flavor.

title: pink lady
directions: Dissolve jello in warm water.
Mix cake mix, oil and eggs together.
Add jello and 1/2 frozen strawberries.
Beat 2 minutes and bake in a baking dish for 25 minutes.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on pkg.
Then drain. Brown ground beef along with onion, green pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain off as much fat as possible from cooked meat mixture.
Add the cooked meat mixture to cooked pasta.
Add the tomato soup and both cans of chopped tomatoes. (Do not drain the chopped tomatoes.)	Mix all ingredients together.
Heat on low on top of stove until good and hot.
Before serving, you may sprinkle on cheese.	Makes 4 generous servings.
Goes well with a salad and hot corn bread.

title: apple-spice loaf
directions: Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nutmeg. Stir together egg whites, brown sugar, apple, oil and orange peel. Mix flour mixture into apple mixture just until combined.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray coating.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheddary pasta and vegetables
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add carrots, broccoli and peppers for last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.

title: cream caramels
directions: Bring to boil 1 cup of cream, sugar, Karo and butter.
Stir continuously, then slowly pour in second cup of cream (add slowly).
Continue to stir until thick; don't let it stop boiling to medium ball stage.
Testing as it darkens and thickens.
Butter pan and pour into pan.
Let cool, then cover with paper, foil or plastic.

title: ever ready muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; mix well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake a few at a time if needed.
Fill muffin tins (greased or lined with paper cups) 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onions in 6 tablespoons butter.
Blend in salt and flour.
Add milk.
Cook until sauce is smooth and thick.
Stir in cheese, crab meat, shrimp, hot sauce and lemon juice.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and stir in crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in food processor and chop well. Add oil slowly, then add Parmesan cheese.

title: clam casserole
directions: Add milk to soup.
Beat eggs.
Crumb crackers.
Melt butter (or margarine).
Mix all the ingredients together well.
Put into a casserole; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix margarine and dressing crumbs; add all other ingredients. Mix thoroughly and bake until done.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in well-greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn cake on cake
plate
and let cool. Sift confectioners sugar on top or frost
with
cream cheese frosting. Makes about 10 servings.

title: hawaiian baked chicken
directions: In 1/4 cup melted butter, quickly brown the chicken on both sides.
Place in a single layer in a baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Brush with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan the pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 400° and cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone and cut into small pieces. Add Pepperidge Farm and herb dressing.
Mix and add butter.
Put mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and then layer deboned chicken.
Mix cans of cream of chicken, mushroom and broth, then pour over top of mixture, then add rest of dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 minutes. Rub butter on crust immediately after taking out of oven.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Beat 10 minutes. Spoon into greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: apricot snowballs
directions: Put apricots through medium blade of food grinder.
Mix ground apricots with coconut, granulated sugar and orange juice.
Blend well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Store in tightly covered container.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: brandy carrots
directions: Melt butter. Add remaining ingredient in a Pyrex baking dish, covered.
Place in oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange-almond salad
directions: In a screw top jar, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and almond extract.
Cover and shake well to dissolve sugar and salt. Chill.

title: carrots
directions: Cook until all liquid is cooked out.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts according to directions for filled one-crust pie using 9-inch pie pan; flute as desired.
In medium bowl stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust-line pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes one (9-inch) pie.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut chicken in 1/4-inch pieces.
Toss chicken, cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of white pepper.
Heat wok and add 1 tablespoon vegetable oil; rotate wok to cover sides.
Add eggs; cook and stir until eggs are thickened but moist.
Remove eggs from wok.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to wok and rotate to coat sides.
Add chicken and stir-fry until done.
Add bean sprouts, mushrooms and 1/2 teaspoon salt; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove from wok.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to wok.
Add rice and stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir in soy sauce and dash of white pepper.
Add chicken mixture, eggs and green onions.
Stir-fry 30 seconds.
Makes 5 servings.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted oleo.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not bake.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in crackers, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in a pie plate that has been greased with Pam or Crisco (no butter).
Cook 30 to 35 minutes on 350°.
Cool and cover with Cool Whip.

title: cheese roll
directions: Combine ingredients; shape into a roll.
Roll in paprika and refrigerate until firm.
Slice.
Cut in 32 slices.

title: cajun snack
directions: Mix crackers and oil in baking pan.
Stir well to coat crackers.
Add seasoning and mix well.
Bake until oil is absorbed and crackers are crispy, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: white bean garlic dip
directions: In a medium size pan over medium to low heat, cook beans and garlic until beans are tender, (30 to 45 minutes).
Once beans are tender, remove garlic.
Place beans in food processor, add lemon juice and a pinch of salt.
Puree 3 to 4 minutes, then add olive oil and puree 2 additional minutes.
Slice and toast the bread. Spread bean dip on toast, sprinkle with sage and serve.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Beat heavy cream in a cool bowl with cool beaters.
Slowly add confectioners sugar to taste.
Add vanilla.
Beat 5 to 8 minutes to right consistency.
Fold in drained fruit cocktail and chopped nuts.
Put in pie crust.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix together pineapple, sugar, flour and cheese.
Place mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover top with cracker crumbs and drizzle with melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch glass pie pan.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Bake approximately 50 to 55 minutes.

title: angel
directions: Mix crackers and nuts and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Add to crackers and nuts and mix well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Cool Whip over top and coconut. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: sugar-free fruit tart
directions: *Two tablespoons apricot fruit spread combined with 1 tablespoon warm water.

title: another garlic soup recipe(serving size:  6)
directions: Combine garlic and onion in a bowl. Heat oil in a large pot. Add garlic and onion; saute until soft. Do not brown. Add chopped tomatoes and stir in well. After a few minutes, stir in stock and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes. Add salt, if desired. Serve with croutons.

title: kentz cole slaw
directions: Bring oil, vinegar, sugar and salt to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, chopped bell pepper and onions.
Stir in celery seed. Refrigerate overnight or 6 to 8 hours.

title: amish easy pie filling cake
directions: Cream together shortening and butter.
Add sugar gradually. Add eggs.
Beat well and add flour gradually.
Spread mixture in 13 x 9-inch greased pan saving 1/2 cup of dough.
Spread 1 can apple pie filling and top with drops of remaining dough and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cake is still warm, spread with powdered sugar.

title: broiled beef ribs - korean style
directions: Choose beef ribs with little gristle or fat and cut into 3 to 4-inch lengths.

Score each piece of meat deeply with a sharp knife several times so cooked meat will be easier to remove from bone. Combine all other ingredients, except onion and bell pepper, and pour mixture over meat pieces, rubbing together with hands so beef ribs are well coated with seasonings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes, then microwave sweet potatoes and butter in a bowl until soft enough to mash. Add 4 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Mix well with mixer and place in small casserole dish. Place remaining milk and butter along with brown sugar and pecans in a pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake - karen's
directions: Combine the 1 1/2 cups sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and melted shortening or butter.
Grease pan and pat in pan.

title: strawberry pretzels
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix well and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Whip well.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spread evenly over pretzel mixture, making sure sides are sealed.
Mix the jello and water.
Add strawberries to the jello.
Pour this over the whipping cream mixture.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix ingredients all together and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
This is a 100 year old recipe.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let set until double in bulk.
Knead dough.
Roll out on floured surface and cut rolls with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan; brush tops of rolls with oil and let rise again. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Beat powdered sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla together.
Cover graham cracker crumb layer.
Slice bananas on top of this mixture. Cover bananas with the crushed pineapple and top this with large container of Cool Whip.
Chill 5 hours.
Enjoy.

title: creole wieners
directions: Fry bacon and onions in 10-inch skillet until bacon is crisp and onions are tender.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon fat in skillet.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally 15 minutes.
Add wieners, cover and simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: tarragon-raisin chicken salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine chicken, salt, onion, carrot and peppercorns.
Add water to cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is cooked through.
Strain broth. (Freeze for future use.)
Cut chicken into large chunks and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, tarragon and raisins.
Add to chicken and mix until chicken is well coated.
Serves 4.

title: coffee and marshmallow pudding
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in coffee in a double boiler.
Let marshmallows cool and add whipped cream and vanilla.
Serve cold.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: cheesy ham sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together ham, process cheese spread, mayonnaise and onion.
Place 1/3 cup of mixture on bottom of each bun.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and process cheese spread begins to melt.
Makes 8 sandwiches.
Preparation time:
20 minutes; cooking time:
15 minutes.

title: avocado spread
directions: Mash avocados until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except crackers.
Garnish with snipped parsley or paprika, if desired.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of spread.

title: ras-malai dessert
directions: Mix sugar and Ricotta cheese and bake at 250° until top turns light brown.
Pour half and half over it and sprinkle with powdered pistachio.
Chill well before serving.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Cut each breast into lengthwise strips.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

Heat oil in frypan over medium heat. Add chicken and brown. Cook asparagus 3 to 4 minutes following package directions. Drain. Stir together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Place asparagus in single layer in shallow baking pan. Place chicken over asparagus.
Spoon on sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, honey, eggs and raisins.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 300° for about an hour.
It is good hot or cold and even better topped with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix
mushroom soup and chicken soup with melted cheese. Cook broccoli, then drain well.
Place broccoli in oblong pan; pour cheese
mixture
over
top, then bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes, take
out
and crumble onion rings on top, then bake for 5 more minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper; drain.
Mix with spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
In separate container, mix cottage cheese, Parmesan and Mozzarella with eggs.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and peanut butter. Stir in egg, milk and vanilla. In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Shape dough into 42 balls. Roll balls in additional sugar. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes. Remove from oven. Press a Kiss gently into the center. Return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes. Cool at least 1/2 hour.

title: chicken diable(serves 4)
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry and remove skin (if you want).
Melt butter in shallow baking pan; stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll chicken pieces in mixture to coat all over.
Arrange meaty side up in a single layer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and richly glazed.

title: big red sherbet
directions: Combine ingredients and put in ice cream freezer. Freeze.
